text:
What a fun time! We had the best experience axe throwing! From the moment we walked in to the time we left, everything was positive, fun, and just a great time all around. The woman who checked us in was so sweet and immediately made us feel welcome‚Äîshe joked around with us and set the tone for the night.

The bartenders and servers were awesome, and super friendly. We were honestly surprised by how good the food was ‚Äî it was way better than we expected! Usually places like this don‚Äôt focus much on food, but this was honestly better than a lot of sit-down restaurants we‚Äôve been to.

The axe throwing coaches were super helpful, and fun to talk to. You could tell they really enjoyed what they do. Honestly, every single employee we interacted with was great and seemed to love working here.

Highly recommend this place if you‚Äôre looking for something fun, laid-back, and surprisingly delicious! We will most definitely be back!

title: McDonald's (Bonney Rd)
address: 4696 Bonney Rd, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text:
A Solid and Speedy Stop on Independence Blvd.
This particular McDonald's has become my reliable go-to for a quick and satisfying meal, especially when I'm on the move along the busy Independence corridor. The standout feature here is undoubtedly the efficiency of their drive-thru service. Even during what appears to be a chaotic lunch rush, the line moves along at a commendably brisk pace, and the staff manages to remain composed and friendly.
On my most recent visit, my order of a Quarter Pounder with Cheese and a side of their classic fries was delivered promptly and accurately. The burger was hot and fresh, and the fries had that perfect level of crispiness and salt. It‚Äôs this consistency that keeps me coming back; you know exactly what you're going to get, and it rarely disappoints. The convenience of its location is another major plus, making it an easy pit stop whether you're heading to the interstate or running errands in the area.
The reason for withholding that final star is the occasional inconsistency with the cleanliness of the dining area during peak times. While generally well-maintained, there have been a couple of instances where finding a completely clean table required a bit of a search. However, this is a minor critique of what is otherwise a very well-run and dependable McDonald's. For a quick, classic, and efficient fast-food experience, this location certainly delivers.

text:
This was not a visit that I was expecting only because I usually do not dine in. A friend and I went in, and she got the Fish-fil-a large combo with sweet tea, and I got a Fish-fil-a sandwich only. She asked for no tarter sauce, and I asked for extra. I also asked them to make them fresh so I wouldn't have to wonder if they were fresh or not. We sat in the dining area for over 15 minutes, and a lady asked us if we had received our food yet. We both shook our heads and said no, and she was baffled to where our food was and why it was taking so long. Yes, it was lunch time, and the drive-thru was around the building, but inside was only us and 3 other people. She came back out 5 minutes later and apologized. My friend opened her fish, and hers had tarter, mustard, and mayo on it. Mine was to my liking. BUT, we came together and I was not going to eat in front of her and she had tea to drink only! So, the lady said that they would remake them both and it wouldn't take too long. She brought them out within 7 minutes, and her fries were not fresh. At this point, I had no patience for this, and I asked her, "What is going on?" She was the Mgr. and said that they had an influx of door dash and drive-thru orders that the cook was simply overloaded and offered us a blizzard. Well, my friend took one, but I can't have sugar, so I was fine. My issue is going inside to eat is not like when we were kids! They pay no attention to the customers, and they are understaffed at a time when they should have plenty of people to handle a lunch time!
Nevertheless, I will not be wasting my time in this establishment again. It's just not worth it! BTW, a combo for her was $17.29, and my total was, I believe, $6.14! WOW, I know it is expensive to eat out, but McDonalds has taken it to a whole other level of expensive! SMH üòï üòî

text:
Burger King: A Heartbreaking Decline in Quality**

I have watched the steady decline of Burger King's product quality over the past year and more, and my recent visit to the location at Comanche Road and Princess Anne Road  Virginia Beach has left me truly disheartened.

Once, their chicken breakfast sandwiches were generously sized, often rivaling the burgers themselves and extending to the edges of the buns, biscuits, or croissants. Now, what I received was nothing short of a ripoff: the chicken was alarmingly small‚Äîbarely larger than a chicken nugget. For a price that keeps climbing, the portion sizes have shrunk drastically.

This is why businesses like Chick-fil-A continue to outshine and outpace Burger King. I feel taken advantage of, and as a result, I requested a refund. I will never patronize Burger King again. It‚Äôs time for Burger King to address this issue and return to the quality and portion sizes that loyal customers deserve.

text: My family has vacationed at Sandbridge for 36 years.  Always played a few rounds of golf at the nearby Hells Point course.  The last few years that course went downhill and prices doubled.  We decided to try other nearby courses.  Cypress Point CC is by far a better course.  Well maintained.  Actually has grass on the tee boxes and they regularly relocate the holes unlike Hells Point that I think the holes are still in the same as they were last year.  Fun course for half the price too.  If you are vacationing at Sandbridge or VA Beach I highly recommend Cypress Country Club

title: Cypress Point Country Club
address: 5340 Club Head Rd, Virginia Beach, VA 23455
text:
The course was in great shape and has a forgiving layout. Rough is cut a bit high and sometimes you can't see the ball until you stand right over it. Fairways are mostly soft so don't expect much rollout. It's a fairly short course so not that big a problem. I had no issue making greens in regulation even playing off their back tees. Greens are extremely slow and soft (plugged a wedge shot in the center of a green on #8). Speed is so slow; I would guess under 8 on a stimpmeter but they do roll true and are easy to read. All-in-all a decent experience. Course allowed me to score at my handicap my first time playing.
Pros
1. Great staff all around
2. Everything is green and well-manicured
3. Electric carts are in great shape (would be nice if they had GPS)
Cons
1. No sand in the sand jars (club employee stated they haven't had sand since covid)
2. Lots of ball marks left unrepaired on greens and footsteps not raked in traps
3. Driving range was closed before my tee time because the collector wasn't connected to the tractor to collect balls

title: Sonic Drive-In
address: 4889 Virginia Beach Blvd, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text: Waited 30 minutes for our food and drinks that I had ordered on the app. I waited 20 minutes but after seeing cars who came after me get their food, I pushed the button to ask how much longer and the dude responded sarcastically saying he knows we had been waiting that they wanted everything to come out together. Fast-forward another 5 minutes and this girl named Taylor? brought out a bag, asked if we had ordered the items she had, and I told her yes and 3 drinks; she only had food so she said that she would go get them. I touched the food and asked how long they had been sitting there because they were cold. She responsed sarcastically saying that "as you can see" they are extremely busy and I said I understood that but that I had waited 25 minutes for our order and it was cold. She started getting an attitude with me, I interrupted and asked how I could get a refund and she told me to go through the app. I told her to just get the drinks and I would use the app. She got an attitude and shook her head, then held a finger out and walked inside. She brought the drinks out then said sarcastically "Have a nice day." I understand restaurants get busy but there is no excuse for a fast food restaurant to take 30 minutes to bring an order out; cold food is not excusable and rudeness and sarcasm is DEFINITELY NOT okay. I have given this location SOOO many chances but this was the last straw. If you're local to Virginia Beach, go to the Sonic on Nimmo Parkway; we have never had an issue with them and they are very polite and have excellent customer service skills!

title: Sunrise Pizza Restaurant
address: 4848 Virginia Beach Blvd #1, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text:
Sunrise Pizza is located along Virginia Beach Blvd. in the Aragona Village Shopping Center in Virginia Beach.  I had heard about the place through an ad on Facebook and decided to try them out sometime.  My visit here was on August 30, 2025.

I had gotten here around 3:45 pm, so parking wasn't an issue.  Since it is in a shopping center, parking tends to be available.  They are on the corner end of the shopping center.  The inside of the place is pretty simple.  There is seating available, as well as the pick-up and ordering counter for to-go orders.

My mom and I decided to dine in, and we could choose where to sit.  There wasn't anyone else visiting the place at the time.  Our server came over fairly quickly to get our drink orders and a menu to review.  For those that drink sodas, they carry Pepsi products.  After getting our drinks, she asked if we were ready to order, but we weren't just yet since there was quite a bit to choose from.  After some more time, she came back to us, and we were ready to order.  I ended up getting a Pepperoni Calzone.  My mom went with the Homemade Meatloaf Entree which was on special that day.

A few minutes later, she came back to bring the garden salad and garlic knots that are part of the homemade meatloaf entree.  I did get to try one of the garlic knots and it was really good.  After about 10 minutes or so, the main meals came to the table.  The Pepperoni Calzone looked great, as well as the Homemade Meatloaf entree.  They were both hot when they came out.  The Pepperoni Calzone was really good.  I only had half of it, as I didn't want to overload myself on carbs.  It did end up elevating my blood sugars afterwards, but not significantly higher.  My mom liked the Homemade Meatloaf entree too.

As a part of the coupon I had, I was able to get a free small pizza, which I ordered to-go.  It didn't include any toppings, but I did have pepperoni added to it.  I would have a few slices over a few days.  That pizza was good too.

Overall, this was a good experience here.  They have daily specials, as well as lunch specials if you come in during the lunch hours.  They did well to ensure we had what we wanted and if there were any issues (there were none).  If you are in this part of the city and looking for a pizza type of place, this place is worth checking out.

title: Sunrise Pizza Restaurant
address: 4848 Virginia Beach Blvd #1, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text:
If you haven‚Äôt tried this place yet ‚Äî go now! üçï The pizza is absolutely amazing ‚Äî fresh, cheesy, and full of flavor. The staff is super friendly and genuinely care about their customers, which makes every visit a great experience.

They‚Äôve got plenty of parking (no stress there!), a convenient location right in the heart of Virginia Beach, and a wide variety of food to choose from. Everything is always fresh ‚Äî and all halal, which is really important for our family.

Whether you‚Äôre stopping by for a quick lunch or sitting down for a cozy family dinner, this spot is a total win. Highly recommended! üôå

Huge disappointment for such a large and expensive order.  Manager was not happy that we got free cheese bread even though it was their own coupon from the menu.

title: Boulevard Stop Mart - Krispy Krunchy Chicken
address: 5444 Virginia Beach Blvd # 101, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text:
I was a frequent goer there because I loved the chicken and wedge combo. On a Tuesday close to their closing time, I went because I had a craving for their food. The cook asked me to talk to the cashier for my order. I asked for a breast and wedge order. The cook yelled, ‚ÄúDoes it look like there‚Äôs breasts here?‚Äù but in a very rude and disrespectful manner. I went back and checked him letting him know that it was a mistake not realizing there wasn‚Äôt any there, but he needed to watch his tone. He preceded to ignore what I was saying, being obnoxious about it. The cashier was very gracious, asking me what I wanted, but I decided to get my money back because customer service like that cook gave should not be rewarded under any circumstance. I will always like the brand, but I won‚Äôt frequent this branch again because there was no reason for him to be so snarky like he was.

People need to keep in mind that if a place is going to be great, especially one that sells food, the cook has to be cordial to its customers as well or else they will lose business. The food will always be great, but that service was beyond unacceptable.

title: Pho 79
address: 4816 Virginia Beach Blvd, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text:
I‚Äôve been eating at Pho79 on Va. Beach Blvd for 20 years because their food has always been good. Atmosphere is just okay but that is not important here in this review. ‚ÄúThe service‚Äù last night was rude and awful. My friend and I walked in at 7:29pm, hours on door says open to 8pm. The closing manager came over and knows I‚Äôm a regular and said ‚ÄúDo you know we close at 8pm?‚Äù He was clearly agitated that we were there. I said yes,  I‚Äôm aware and that is why we came at 7:30pm. We ordered without looking at the menu immediately. He never asked how we were, no smile just plainly agitated that we came. There were 6 other occupied tables when we arrived.
At 7:55pm all tables had left except for us and one other table of 2.  We were only half finished with our small bowls of soup.  We were rushing the whole time, their soup is always hot and even though the soup tasted amazing we wanted to leave from there, due to feeling like the manager did not want us.  So, at 7:55pm paid $31 for 2 small bowls of soup and asked for soup containers to take home the leftovers. I wrapped the sprouts and basil in napkins, no box was given for that and we left.
So here is My Suggestion, Pho lock your doors at 7pm or 7:30pm, so No new customers can enter. This way the closing manager and staff can leave by 8pm. Keep the inside door handle unlocked so inside guests can leave. If you keep offending your regulars or any customers they will stop coming. One more incident, the busser who was cleaning tables bumped the heavy cart on wheels so hard into my booth seat, that my whole seat moved out of place with me in it. Never said sorry, never asked if I was okay?
I‚Äôm a former server and both behaviors are offensive and unacceptable.  Obviously customers at this location are not valued. Just Lock your doors at 7p or 7:30p to keep your customers from coming into eat, so you can go home exactly at 8pm. We sat in the car and watched the last table leave at 8p and the closing manager walked out a few minutes after that.

title: Pho 79
address: 4816 Virginia Beach Blvd, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text:
The place was not very welcoming. As soon as I walked in, I was greeted, but the son of whomever worked there (must've been in his 20s but clearly had a mental disability so I don't fault him in particular)  started yelling out loud and touching my missing arm as I was trying to order. Not a single worker intervened or apologized or anything. I then decided to just brush it off as it is definitely the people around him that have failed him.

Now on to the ordering process. I originally asked for 2 small #4 bowls with spring rolls. The man up front told me that they did not have any smalls (I looked at pictures of the menu, and it had them there, but I was not gonna press the issue), I reluctantly asked for larges instead until I found out it was going to be $50.

Mind you, I am an optimist, so I am still fine with the strangness, and I opt to just get 1 large.

Now, the weirdest thing happened while I was sitting down. First, though, I wanna say I am not making any accusations or assumptions, just mearly going to write down what I saw. An older caucasian gentleman walked in with a young vietnamese girl. He then started yelling for the older lady in the back, asking where she was. A different man walked out from the back and told him to shush while waving him over. They then spoke quietly amongst themselves while seemingly aware I was watching, and then the old lady came out as well. The caucasian man saw her and said, "Here you go! She is all yours now!" and walked out.

I will reiterate that I am not making any assumptions and only typing what I witnessed.

Finally, the food. The broth was a lot more "gingery" than I am used to with pho, and the beansprouts had a funky smell. The only saving grace was the fresh spring rolls, which is why I gave them 2 stars for food but 1 star for everything else.

Safe to say, I will never be coming back. It even prompted me to write a review, which I almost never do.

text: Do not order delivery from this place. We ordered and paid in advance (over 24 hours in advance) 4 pizzas to be delivered to my 6 year-olds birthday party by 4:00 pm. We had to be out of the venue by 4:30 pm. At 4:00 we get a call from a driver saying he can't find the place, but he coukd hardly speak English, so we could not tell him how to get there. We texted him the address again and called the store. We were told by the manager that they would put some pizzas in and drive them over themselves. At 4:20 I called back because we were 10 minutes from having to send 15 kids home hungry. I was told that they don't have any drivers and had to send it with their "partner" grubhub. If I wanted to count on a gig worker, I would have ordered from grubhub. At 4:30 the original guy l finally found it with our original pizzas that he was driving around with for 40 minutes. Luckily, the venue allowed us to extend our stay there so the kids finally got fed, but we missed half of our daughters party dealing with this mess. It is inexcusable to have a pizzaria that can't deliver a pizza.

text:
Update:4/19/24 - I just decided to give another try to this business. Disappointed again.. I ordered what they call the Pizzoli, which is not on the website. I ordered the buffalo chicken with light sauce simialr to pizza roll or wrap. I received a roll filled with cheese, no buffalo sauce and what appears to be three small stripes of chicken with a little cup of ranch I did ask for. The whole roll was roughly less than 5 inches for $7+ dollars... There will not be a third time!!! SEE photos.

Initial post:
Well, this is a new location..... Now I would have given them 4 stars for cleanliness, for not letting the cook do the register or folding boxes or doing anything else without thoroughly washing hands up to the elbow. Great!!!  This was a good thing! Now the food on the other hand. I just ordered the Pizza bowl and wings. The Wings 4 Stars. The bowl was supposed to be a two-serving bowl based on the writing on the menu. Well to my surprise, it was not and only enough to cover the bottom of the plastic black bowl and not even half full.  This should have been double the contents if was to be a two-serving bowl for the price as advertised. I am nearly done with just three quick scoops, so glad I ordered wings I would have been still hungry. This was and is only enough for one serving or person. Even if they had put another $1 on the price and added more toppings to be two-servings.  That would have been perfect.

text: So we gave this specific location one last chance and will never return again.  The first time we went our order was given to someone else by mistake so we waited for it to be remade. I asked if my order had been sitting for the 3 hours as I had received an email shortly after that I placed it that it was ready.  So he proceeded to locate my order.  I think they were still making it.  Then today, I ordered the food on the Marco app around 1pm to pick up at 5:35pm. textTranslated:
Review of Pho 79 Restaurant: An Unforgettable Experience

When choosing a place to enjoy pho on the weekend, my family decided to stop by Pho 79 with the hope of finding not only delicious bowls of pho but also a warm, friendly welcome. However, our experience was not as expected.

From the moment we stepped into the restaurant, we felt the cold, unwelcoming atmosphere. The attitude of the waiters was even worse: no greetings, no minimal attention that you would expect from a restaurant. With just a gesture, they signaled us to sit down without any warmth or invitation.

When receiving the menu, there was no introduction or inquiry about the drinks or dishes that we wanted to try. Everything happened mechanically, making us feel like we were not welcome here.

I have visited many pho restaurants around the world and always appreciate politeness and friendliness from the staff. This not only makes the food more delicious but also makes the dining experience more memorable. Unfortunately, Pho 79 did not do that.

The experience at Pho 79 left us with a not-so-positive impression. It was not only the disappointment in the service, but also the feeling of not being appreciated as the guests should be treated. Hopefully, the restaurant will realize and improve its service level so that no one else has to go through the same feelings.

This review is based on your personal experience and feelings, highlighting the problems you encountered when eating at the restaurant. Hopefully, it will help the restaurant owner to be aware and improve their service in the future.

title: Wingstop
address: 928 Diamond Springs Rd Ste 105, Virginia Beach, VA 23455
text:
We Love the wings but the service has made us not want to return. We have been twice since the beginning of January to get wings for football games.

The service at the pickup counter was absolutely horrible. We went on the night on the 1st and 10th of the month. The lack of attentiveness, and blatant rudeness. Was unacceptable. As a former industry worker, and manager, I was appalled at the treatment myself and other customers around us received for simply picking up orders. We waited close to 10min without a single employee acknowledging us and when trying to speak we were told "hold on, we're busy" while they went back to talking amongst themselves.

The FOH needs a lot more training on how to greet customers at the door, simply acknowledging guests when they walk in, asking them what they need and being kind.

We will be finding another wing place for future events and family dinners.

text:
If I could rate 0, I would. I ordered $50+ worth of chicken that had a fishy taste to it. I called the store, and the young lady informed me that the grease might need to be refreshed but only the manager could do that. I spoke to the manager, Dashawn, who seems like a nice guy but has given me the runaround regarding my refund and has not communicated in a few days. Every time I call the store, he's not available nor returns my calls. He originally stated he would resolve it within 72 hours after forwarding it to the regional manager. I have escalated it to corporate and am waiting for their follow-up. Let's see how fast they move. Run from this establishment. Please believe the reviews; I should have. It's been 9 days without resolution so that should tell you how they feel about their customers!!!

Update: I contacted corporate through their Facebook page, and they sent me a gift card for the amount I spent. I will use it at a different location, and I made that known to them.

She went and got the guy named que...he sd you never ordered 2 large and 1 medium drink. He argued with me about it. Showed the screeb but i never got my receipt or asked if i wanted it. When i got home with my order the fries on all the orders were cold. Barely edible. The wings were decent. I work at a restaurant and we have to cover our hair to avoid getting hair in the food. Update: corp posted something on there facebook page. I told them how is $5 gonna do something when i spent almost $40 at the store. They wanted to see how much i spent. I screenshotted a copy from my bank statement since store refused to give me receipt. Corp ended up giving me a $40 gift card.
Im ordering again tonight lets see how it goes. Ill be posting another review.

title: Town Center Cold Pressed - Virginia Beach Town Center
address: 168 Central Park Ave, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text:
I hang out at Cold Pressed on my 30 minutes break from work and it is by far my favorite place at town center to spend time at. The staff are extremely friendly and learn your name if you‚Äôre a regular. I‚Äôm always greeted when I walk in no matter how busy it is. The coffee is consistently good and the vibe is very warm and cozy.

The only thing I think could improve the experience is getting rid of the touch kiosks. It is fairly easy to use, and while I understand the need for them for busy periods, it lacks the personal touch. I love ordering with a real person and often am able to use my rewards points easier.

I think Cold Pressed has improved dramatically and leadership is taking steps to make the store a hub for community connection and I think that‚Äôs beautiful. It‚Äôs really really nice visiting a coffee shop where the baristas know your name and ask how your day is going.

text: I haven't eaten from a Wing Stop location in years due to a bad experience, but I decided to give it a try. I went inside the restaurant to order and was greeted by the most polite staff member. He was very friendly and kindly took my order. Great experience so far! I ordered the mild wings with fries and a drink. Unfortunately, I went home to eat the food and was very disappointed with the wings. It literally tasted like oil, water, and very little sauce. The ranch was the only reason I was able to eat the chicken, in addition to my own hot sauce. I reached out to the company through the website to share my experience and they were amazing! I received a gift card from them and decided to try again but a different flavor. So I went in and had the same good customer service experience and picked up the order of classic Cajun wings and Cajun fries with cheese and ranch sauce. This time, I was very impressed with the food!! It was fresh, cooked just right, and the flavor was most certainly poppin! I loved how it had a lil spice to it as well! I'm grateful that the company responded well and provided me with the gift card to give it another try! But I most certainly hope they improve that mild sauce so that others don't have the same experience! The fries were always good though!!

text:
My mother and I went in yesterday to order and I think that was our first mistake. Everyone that came is was picking up an order and didn't order drinks. I don't think anyone ever does just based on how disgusting the drink machine was. There is mold literally caked on the bottom draining area and all around the center ice machine and black flakes in the ice. The floor was slippery in the dining area as if they either never cleaned it before or used a dirty mop bucket from the kitchen grease.
The biggest issue to me was we asked the girl at the register if the mild sauce had dairy because I'm breast feeding and the baby has a severe allergy to dairy (which I disclosed to her) and she gave me a crazy look and said "no, of course not. I have a dairy allergy too so trust me". While waiting, it didn't sit right with me so I pulled up the nutritional facts on their website and sure enough, mild sauce does have dairy. I had to hurry and change the order.
This is already 2 lawsuits in the making on their part and I will be contacting the health department about it. Working in the food industry and seeing THAT much mold made me sick and I'm sure has actually made several people sick.
Steer clear of this place guys. Seriously.
The chicken wings were over cooked too, nothing worth risking your health and safety over unless you want an easy lawsuit.

title: El Rodeo Mexican Restaurant
address: 5834 E Virginia Beach Blvd, Norfolk, VA 23502
text:
While painting Crunch Fitness in the adjacent shopping center, we decided to stop by El Rodeo Norfolk for lunch ‚Äî and we are so glad we did! From the very beginning, they treated us like family. Since that first visit, it‚Äôs become our new favorite Mexican spot in the area.

Despite countless visits since then, the food and experience have remained consistently great. In fact, it‚Äôs only gotten better. The more we come, the more the staff get to know us, and each visit feels friendlier than the last. On one of our recent visits, we even exchanged canned goods with the staff ‚Äî which truly speaks to the welcoming atmosphere here.

The food and drinks are excellent, and the portion sizes are huge. We always end up taking leftovers home and getting at least two meals out of one visit thanks to their generosity. El Rodeo Norfolk is more than just a restaurant ‚Äî it‚Äôs an experience. We‚Äôll definitely keep coming back and highly recommend it to anyone looking for delicious Mexican food and a place where you feel like part of the family.

title: El Rodeo Mexican Restaurant
address: 5834 E Virginia Beach Blvd, Norfolk, VA 23502
text:
Good enough Mexican food, but not for anyone who cares about value. I‚Äôm a native Texan‚Äînot a professional critic, but I‚Äôve eaten at enough good Mexican spots to know the difference.

Staff were kind, though a bit disengaged. Portions were generous, but the food itself was a 5/10 at best‚Äîmore reminiscent of what I‚Äôve had at a small town in the middle of Germany (not joking) than what I‚Äôd expect here. Just sayin'. At these prices, I expected more heart and passion in the cooking.

I left full, but not impressed. The food solved my hunger pains, but not much more. What really stung was the mismatch between price and plate‚Äîit left me questioning how Google ratings get so inflated.

If you‚Äôre fine paying above-average prices for average beans, rice, ground beef, and cheese, this place will work. But if you‚Äôre chasing the kind of Mexican food that justifies its cost, you‚Äôll want to keep looking.

That's unfortunate...I was really eager to get some good Mexican food too.

Reply to response:

Thank you for your response‚Äîit‚Äôs clear you care about reviews. I respect that your restaurant has been around for 35 years; that shows loyalty and hard work. My feedback isn‚Äôt about wanting something free. It‚Äôs about balance: the prices charged versus the passion and care on the plate.

Right now, the food feels standard‚Äîbeans, rice, beef, cheese‚Äîwhile the prices sit in the ‚Äúpremium‚Äù range. If the cost were lower, I‚Äôd call it fair. At this price point, I expected more heart and bold flavor.

Something has to give: either elevate the quality to match the price, or lower the cost to match the quality. Not doing so risks losing ground to other options nearby. Your reputation was built on higher standards than what I tasted, and I‚Äôd like to see that legacy shine again.

This isn‚Äôt a complaint, it‚Äôs honest feedback. With more care in the kitchen, your food could truly justify its cost and reflect the quality your history deserves.

title: Captain D's
address: 6667 E Virginia Beach Blvd, Norfolk, VA 23502
text:
I‚Äôm an Uber Eats delivery driver. Went to pick up and order and was under the impression order was accurate and filled. Got to the person to whom I was delivering to (IE the original customer) and discovered only 2 of the 3 meals were within the bag given.

I would have easily gone back to the store to simply picked up any remaining food I may have missed, and would not have had any issues driving back to it‚Ä¶had the girl who picked up the phone not hung up on me. Twice.

The second I introduced myself as the driver delivering from Uber Eats, the phone audibly is heard clicking; the line went dead.

Second time I call, they are in mid laughter from what I assume may have been about something else at work (yet is still not professional to hear on the line) and I try to reintroduce myself again. Full name and as ‚Äòthe driver from Uber Eats‚Äô.

Hung up again.

I don‚Äôt appreciate given the feeling of mockery while you can‚Äôt even act professional long enough to meet me halfway on a simple error. I don‚Äôt understand what I did wrong to deserve being made fun of on the phone. You not only mocked me for calling but the customer who now can‚Äôt even have a completed delivery.

This was at around 6pm today, October 5th, 2024.

Edit: Considering neither corporate nor the management ever replied to me when I was asked to send this to their website I will assume either they will not do anything about the issue with their workers or refuse to. My review and grade will remain as such.

title: California Pizza Kitchen
address: 200 Central Park Ave, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text:
On November 29, 2025, my family (party of 11) experienced discriminatory and extremely unprofessional treatment at this California Pizza Kitchen location. From the moment we arrived, the service we received was noticeably different from what was being provided to other guests.

We were told the wait would be 30 minutes, which we respected. After the full wait, we were informed that our table was being delayed because a party who had already paid was ‚Äúlingering.‚Äù When I asked to be seated at a table for 10 instead, the host refused until we said we would leave, and suddenly we were seated immediately.

Once at the table, our server became rude and dismissive toward my aunt after hearing her speak with a Spanish accent. Requests for basic items like bread and drinks were ignored or significantly delayed (bread didn‚Äôt come until after our food arrived). When we asked for a manager, we received a generic apology with no real effort to address the issue.

To make matters worse, the manager then assigned us a new server who approached the table speaking only Spanish despite the fact that I did not speak Spanish to the manager, I do not have a Spanish accent, and nearly half of our table does not speak Spanish. This confirmed that we were being judged based on our appearance and perceived ethnicity.

Cultural disrespect and discriminatory assumptions have no place in customer service or anywhere. Our evening was overshadowed by bias and unprofessionalism, and we left feeling unwelcome. I hope this management team takes this seriously and provides proper training for their staff.

text: Been coming to Q-Masters for several years and dont have a single bad thing to say about the place. The staff is great and the atmosphere is always quite pleasant. If you're looking for a loud, obnoxious bar scene with a pool table or 2 that are crammed into a place thats too small to move around the tables then I'm sorry to inform you that this is NOT it. However, if you ARE looking for a place with plenty of room to move, decent and non-offensive music being played loud enough to be heard but not so loud that you cannot carry on a conversation, clean bathrooms, meticulously maintained tables and equipment and a staff that is as respectful and professional as possible then you've definitely found it. The only things required are that you operate with the same level of respect towards them as they give to you, respect the equipment and other patrons around you. I this place and look forward to many more years ahead.

title: Boss Queens Soul Cafe
address: 5802 E Virginia Beach Blvd #140, Norfolk, VA 23502
text:
Went here Sunday after church around 12:30 pm. No wait time and the restaurant was not busy at all. I came here hoping my experience would be better than the last, but that was not the case at all. I ordered from their apparent ‚Äúnew‚Äù brunch menu and was excited because the options all sounded delicious. My excitement quickly went away from the wait time for our food, which was ridiculous (0/10) especially when the restaurant wasn‚Äôt busy at all. There was also inconsistency among the presentation of food on each plate brought to the table.

I first asked for a mock tail, the Burner (8/10) it was refreshing and I wanted to enjoy it, but the drinks were brought out so quick and our food took 35-40 minutes‚Ä¶ For food, I asked for their Loaded brioche French toast (3/10), the menu stated ‚Äúsweet cream filling‚Äù as if the French toast would be stuffed with the cream inside; however, what I was given was thick slices of dry bread, overly smothered in strawberries, with the tiniest amount of cream thrown on top! No ‚Äúfilling‚Äù in the bread, at all. Bacon (8/10), Grits (9/10), Scrambled Eggs with cheese (4/10) very bland, and Potatoes (2/10) basic, bland, and unseasoned. Additionally, I found out after an order needed to be redone at my table, that my potatoes were actually supposed to come with seasoning and peppers.

My soror who came to brunch with me, had to give her food back after the long wait since her order was not correct at all. What followed, was the manager coming to our table, with what seemed like a bit of an attitude, trying to find out how exactly the order was wrong. While explaining that the French toast didn‚Äôt match the description of the menu, a simple conversation about the menu wording and food outcome/presentation turned into a partial over explaining and back and forth, with the staff almost refusing to accept that what was given to us simply didn‚Äôt match the menu description. After having the waitress and manager come to the table multiple times and after another long wait for food, my Sorors food arrived with an amazing presentation (I should‚Äôve taken a picture of it). Definitely not how my food, my sisters food, or my sorors original plate of food looked at all.

Inconsistency is a major issue here as well as communication. There‚Äôs no reason going back and forth, doing any over explanation, or having to send your food back to be remade should THEN lead to you receiving well prepared/presented food here in this restaurant. The manager explained that the slow service and food presentation was because everyone in the kitchen was being ‚Äútrained‚Äù and the brunch menu was still ‚Äúnew.‚Äù To me, this didn‚Äôt make sense when this restaurant is not new; the explanation/excuse used just didn‚Äôt add up.

Think I‚Äôve given enough chances to this restaurant at this point. I‚Äôve been here some other times and didn‚Äôt do reviews for those experiences, because they weren‚Äôt great, but they also weren‚Äôt terrible, but this recent experience has sealed the deal for me on not coming back; very unfortunate.

The waitress mentioned she would fix our bills to accommodate for the experience we had and while paying, I noticed that the only thing really removed from each bill was basically the tax total.

About $31 spent on my order.

My overall rate of experience : 4/10

text: I must share the wonderful experience with the restaurant today.  I had previously written about an unfortunate experience a couple of weeks ago at this location. I was assured the previous experience was just a one-off unfortunate instance and steps were taken so that it would not be a repeat occurrence.  I and my family left the restaurant today very happy and the food was outstanding.  From the appetizers, through the entries, and finishing with some wonderful desserts. title: Boss Queens Soul Cafe
address: 5802 E Virginia Beach Blvd #140, Norfolk, VA 23502
text:
I came in and was seated immediately, which I appreciated. My server‚Äîher name sounded like Jada, though the music was loud‚Äîcame over about four minutes later to introduce herself. She handed me napkins and silverware and said she‚Äôd be back. She seemed busy, so I understood, but I ended up sitting for about 10 more minutes with no follow-up.

Another server eventually noticed I was still waiting and asked if I had been helped. I explained that my server said she‚Äôd be back. Jada was standing right beside her during that interaction and still didn‚Äôt come over. They seated another party in her section, and I watched her move them and begin taking their order. I overheard her tell them that the person who originally took their order wasn‚Äôt even a server. At that point I thought maybe she‚Äôd realize I had been sitting without even being asked for a drink order.

A few minutes earlier, some staff had a quick meeting near my table about who was taking which tables. I clearly heard them mention my table‚Äî‚Äú34‚Äù‚Äîyet still no one came. Jada continued taking care of other tables, especially larger parties, while I continued to sit unacknowledged.

It honestly felt like I was being ignored because I was dining alone. I‚Äôm actually a very good tipper (even when gratuity is already included), so that was disappointing. After seeing the staff have a small heated discussion about sections and still being overlooked, I felt uncomfortable and decided to leave. At that point it just didn‚Äôt seem worth staying.

Probably won‚Äôt try this place again.

address: 5802 E Virginia Beach Blvd #140, Norfolk, VA 23502
text:
‚≠ê 0/10 for Food ‚Ä¢ ‚≠ê 9/10 for Main Waitress ‚Ä¢ ‚≠ê 0/10 for Food Runner ‚Ä¢ ‚≠ê 8/10 for DJ/Drinks

My family of 20 has visited this restaurant three times in the past two months, and we came again this Friday to celebrate a birthday. We were seated near the bar. I always order the same thing‚Äî the turkey chops ‚Äî because they‚Äôre usually crispy, crunchy, and perfect.

This time, the experience was completely different.

My family‚Äôs food came out fast, so we were excited. But when I started eating, my gravy was freezing cold, like it had come straight out of the refrigerator. I even asked my waitress to touch it so she could feel it for herself, and she immediately apologized and took it back.

When my plate returned, my sides were different than what I ordered. Instead of macaroni and candied yams, it came with yams and collard greens. That wasn‚Äôt a big issue mistakes happen ‚Äî and she did bring out the macaroni afterward. But the turkey wings was still ice cold, Who want a soggy turkey chop ? and the turkey chop I requested ‚Äúfried hard‚Äù was soggy, not crunchy, and clearly not fresh. It tasted like it had been sitting out, not freshly cooked, and the whole plate was cold.

I made sure my waitress knew I wasn‚Äôt upset with her. She was kind, professional, and clearly doing her best. The issue was 100% coming from the kitchen.

What really added to the bad experience was the person helping bring out the food. She was noticeably rude and kept acting irritated any time she had to walk around us ‚Äî even though we were celebrating, dancing, and enjoying ourselves. Instead of walking around to serve people directly, she passed plates over people and had us passing them down the table like it was an offering plate. It felt unprofessional and lazy.

After this visit, I can honestly say I won‚Äôt be returning.
The food was a 0/10, the DJ and drinks were an 8/10, my waitress deserves a 9/10, but the food runner gets a 0/10 for attitude and service.

I would not recommend this location after this experience.

text:
Let‚Äôs just say it‚ÄîI LOVE Q-Masters. It's got everything you‚Äôd want in a great night out: solid drinks, great food, good vibes, and pool tables that practically beg for friendly competition. But the real gem? Marisa the bartender.

Marisa is an absolute rockstar. She‚Äôs patient with the tipsy, kind to the confused, and somehow remembers your drink order after just a couple visits. Don‚Äôt know what you want? No problem‚ÄîMarisa knows what‚Äôll hit the spot. Her suggestions are always on point.

Buy a cocktail, get a free therapy session‚Äîno judgment, just genuine connection. Marisa listens like a friend, mixes like a pro, and makes Q-Masters feel like home.

This bar isn‚Äôt just a hangout‚Äîit‚Äôs a haven. üç∏üé±üí¨

title: Q-Master Billiards
address: 5612 Princess Anne Rd, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text:
Amazing "Old School" PoolHall feel, the place just has an energy about it!
The tables are well taken care of and the balls were like new.

I also got one of my cues re-tipped here and the gentleman running the service shop was a true Professional...he even played his guitar and sung a few songs while I waited for my tip replacement, awesome!

I only had a few adult beverages when I was there, but some of the people around me ordered food and it looked and smelled wonderful.

I also love the wall of pictures of the past US Open Champs, and there were also some old school wooden bleachers in the 9ft table area, I can only imagine the matches people have watched in this venue!

Overall, visiting Q-Master was a great experience.
If you are a "Pool Head" and are visiting Virginia Beach, this is a MUST STOP for you!

I told my husband I was leaving and even though he felt out of place he decided let‚Äôs go to the bar and order food there maybe they will be faster, we went to bar my husband ordered us drinks and tried to be friendly with bartender the bartender was civil but was not as friendly as he was with  the black patrons who came through. I didn‚Äôt want drama so I told my husband pay for everything I will get a box for the food and will never return to this prejudice place again. I don‚Äôt suggest that anyone who is not Black come to this place because you surely. Won‚Äôt be welcomed. Norfolk and this restaurant need to tighten up the city already has nothing to brag on and this restaurant is  not helping.

text:
I really wanted to like Boss Queens Soul Caf√©, but the experience was disappointing from start to finish. text:
MP Island Cafe is an absolute gem for anyone craving authentic West Indian cuisine. From the moment you walk in, you‚Äôre greeted with island vibes ‚Äî reggae colors, tropical d√©cor, and a warm ‚ÄúWah Gwaan‚Äù that makes you feel right at home.

The food is incredible. Their jerk chicken is perfectly seasoned and cooked to perfection ‚Äî smoky, spicy, and tender ‚Äî and the jerk sauce is on another level. They also offer a wide variety of classic Caribbean dishes like saltfish and ackee, dumplings, oxtail, and much more. Every plate tastes homemade and full of flavor.

Beyond the restaurant, MP Island Cafe doubles as a Caribbean grocery store, so you can grab essentials like dasheen bush, yams, or island spices to recreate your favorite meals at home.

If you‚Äôre looking for authentic Caribbean food with great prices, friendly service, and a true island atmosphere, MP Island Cafe is the place to go. Highly recommended!

title: Q-Master Billiards
address: 5612 Princess Anne Rd, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text:
An Amazing Experience at Q-Master Billiards, Virginia Beach

I‚Äôve known about Q-Master Billiards for a long time, and today, after flying in from Vietnam, I drove three hours from Lorton to Virginia Beach just to visit this legendary pool hall. And honestly, it exceeded all my expectations.

The venue boasts 71 high-quality pool tables, all in excellent condition. The space is massive, beautifully decorated, and has a truly American vibe ‚Äî both modern and cozy at the same time. What amazed me the most was the incredibly affordable pricing ‚Äî only $7 for 4 hours of play, even cheaper than many places back in Vietnam.

The food here is also great. I ordered a steak hach√© with fries and a soft drink, all for just $11. The meal was tasty, well-portioned, and served quickly.

Another highlight of the visit was getting the chance to meet and watch some top-level American pool players ‚Äî incredibly skilled and friendly.

Overall, it was a fantastic experience that I‚Äôll never forget. If I ever get the chance, I‚Äôll definitely come back to Q-Master Billiards again!

text:
Haven‚Äôt played in a while but  I found Q Masters, it‚Äôs incredibly large with lots of pool tables of all sizes.  It has that old school vibe except for the smoke and shady characters. It‚Äôs very clean, the staff are nice excellent especially Victoria, she‚Äôs a sweetheart and obviously well liked by the patrons. The prices for the tables are incredible and the food is very good. I‚Äôve decided to join the Bollman League for socialization and to improve my game. They have several leagues apparently.  Maybe I can win a tourney LOL!

I have no qualms about bringing my wife and grandkids here for a night out. Like I said the food is very good and is moderately priced.

I look forward to establishing myself here as a loyal patron.

Thanks Q Masters!

title: Boss Queens Soul Cafe
address: 5802 E Virginia Beach Blvd #140, Norfolk, VA 23502
text:
This is one of my favorite spots since moving to Norfolk!

Pros:  The staff makes you feel like family.  The last time I was there, Kelsey, my favorite staffer, was training the new staff, an excellent example of great service; their menu selections and their Thursday (Karaoke) nights.  The atmosphere feels intimate, fun and leaves you with the feeling that everyone is welcomed.

The menu has an excellent selection and the food choices provides for everyone's taste from the vegan to the meat lovers.

Cons:  (and I only have one), I'm not sure if the chef rotates, but sometimes  (which I didn't experience on my recent visit) certain items can be heavy on the salt.  However, this is easily rectified by requesting that they be light on the salt.

Overall a great place to dine and get a feeling of that "Southern Hospitality!"

title: Boss Queens Soul Cafe
address: 5802 E Virginia Beach Blvd #140, Norfolk, VA 23502
text:
Wish I could give the food a better rating. After arriving with 25 minutes of happy hour left, unexpectedly (it was my first time at this place and didn't pick it out for the happy hour. It was just a nice surprise.), we were excited to try the available items. However, due to the large number of menu items (which all sounded great) plus the additional happy hour menu, we needed time to figure out what wanted.

We ordered get 1 set of happy hour drinks. However, our waitress failed to inform us of the timeline and when we were ready to order happy hour apps, we were informed we were 3 minutes past the cut off for happy hour. So no more happy hour drinks or apps. It would have been nice to have been given the chance to order another round of drinks and be ahead if we'd like to order some food.

So a disappointment starting the night. No big deal! However no consideration was given to our visible disappointment. Instead, "it is what it is" was the atmosphere provided.

We ended up getting 2 appetizers, 1 more round of drinks, then we left because just executing the items ordered took another hour. So no real dinner was had.

I will game this as a learning experience and take accountability for my party's part in this: we should have watched the clock more closely. We got excited and then disappointed, because we didn't know. Guess we know now. But will I want to come back? No, not at this moment.

Expect to spend $30/person for drinks and appetizers. Not bad prices, if you swap out entrees rather than appetizers.

The food we did get was pretty good. Though one of the salmon bites did have a foul odor/taste, indicative of being past its most fresh.

Noise did pick up later in the evening and sounded terrible once the live performers came. I think it wouldn't hurt to consult someone with acoustics knowledge on how to improve the audio experience. My simple suggestion would be to turn it down a notch. Had to yell to hear each other right at our table. The seating and general vibe otherwise were nice. And still enjoyed what we could.

text: I love supporting black owned businesses!!! I am from New Jersey but I live in Pennsylvania my husband and I are out here on vacation in Virginia if I could give this restaurant 20 Stars I would if you want to vibe you definitely need to come here the food and the service was excellent the bathroom is huge the stars are huge the music was great they have a bar they have a stage I mean what don't they have LOL I had the catfish and grits beef sausage with tomatoes my husband had the same except he had Whiting fish the grits was cooked to perfection the only thing was that the Grits had milk in them and I'm lactose intolerant but I still ate them LOL it was so good that I couldn't pass it up let me get back to the vibe dark and Moody but also bright I love the fact that everyone in this restaurant was African-American hats off to the chef they have so many things on the menu and I'm sure they're all delicious I'm talking about the black ceiling black and glitter walls all the African-American art the beautiful chandeliers it's so many good things in here that I can't even think of it all SMH I highly recommend this restaurant oh I forgot to mention 2:00 in the afternoon and the door never stopped opening that's how good the food is people never stop coming I can only imagine what it's like at night time they also have a bar if you want a little drink or cocktail I do highly recommend this restaurant if you ever in Norfolk Virginia you have to stop here if you never heard of it and you live in Virginia you need to Google it!!! oh I forgot to mention the portion size is huge!!!

title: Q-Master Billiards
address: 5612 Princess Anne Rd, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text:
I love this place so much! The biggest pool hall in the US and the original owner founded the US Open 9 Ball tournament, which is the largest running pool tournament globally!

I visited this place on Saturday night (03/22/2025) with a group of 8 to celebrate my birthday. My boyfriend and I arrived at 7:00 PM so we could start waiting for a pool table, and I told my friends to get there at 7:30. I expected to get a table by 7:40 at the latest, but we didn't get one until 8:00 PM. This situation kinda sucked because my friends ended up waiting 30 minutes with us :(. I knew there would be a wait, but I underestimated how long. That's on me for not arriving even earlier.

Once we got our pool table, we waited about 20-30 minutes for a waiter to take our first orders. Some of us went up to the bar to place drink orders instead of waiting. We even asked the front desk about it, but they said the waiters make their rounds and there wasn't much they could do. I really feel like there should be a call light, like there is at Cinema Cafe!

That said, when we finally got our service, our waitress was amazing! She was incredibly kind and patient, even with our group of eight splitting the tab in different ways lol. She made the process smooth and even offered to take a group picture (she wanted to make my birthday memorable), which I really appreciated. The only downside was that my $10 birthday credit didn't apply when she scanned my QR code, and I didn't realize until the next day when I looked at the text receipt. Partly my fault for not noticing and I'm kinda sad I can't use the credit another time due to its expiration date :(

I know this review might come off more negative than positive, but the main reason I'm still giving five stars is because of how great our server was, and because I genuinely LOVE this place :) Everyone had such a fun time (even those who rarely play pool), and honestly this was the best birthday I had in a LONG time!

title: Taco Bell
address: 649 Newtown Rd, Norfolk, VA 23502
text:
Finally!!!

I conducted a very unscientific experiment over the last few months, with what was my last fast food, guilty pleasure- Taco Bell! (Specifically during Nacho Fries season- the only Fries I now ever eat and am willing to waste calories on.)

I sadly thought I was going to give up that last guilty pleasure after sampling food from many of the Taco Bell's in the area over the last few months.  10 locations in 90 days and ONLY ONE of the 10 met, and even surpassed my expectations, of getting fresh, hot, and tasty food! The meal was PERFECT!!!! üòã

I am glad to end this "taco tour" on a high note, and the Newtown Rd location will be the only one I recommend to others, or choose to visit in the future,  the next time I am craving my favorite "4th meal" (as it used to be called back in the day) although it is much more likely to be my first and only meal these days, with the combined constantly busy schedule of being a  caregiver, and the economy making eating out a major expense, that I am giving up from my budget for the upcoming year.

Thank you, kitchen staff at 649 Newtown Rd Norfolk, VA Taco Bell for finally delivering what was the best Taco Bell food, not only in the last several months, but truthfully, in the last few decades!!! They blew everybody else out of the water!!!

Specifically, I had a small order of Nacho Fries (using the Nacho Fries Lover's pass offer) with hot Nacho cheese sauce to dip them in, a Mexican pizza (which was only my 2nd time trying it ever, and which I thought I would never get again,  it was so terrible, soggy and cold the 1st time I got it.) And my last favorite- the Nacho Cheese Doritos Locos Taco Supreme!

As with every other order, I asked if they could please prepare my order fresh after I arrived, and to please drop a fresh batch of fries, so they would be the hot, crispy, perfectly seasoned indulgence worthy of all the oh so bad for me calories and "junk food" cravings that have become fewer and fewer as I have aged.

The Newtown Road location was the ONLY restaurant out of the 10 to prepare my entire order fresh, piping hot, and perfectly portioned, with condiments, drink, napkins, and sauce packets as requested, both in my app order, and when arriving to the restaurant.

It seemed like more than half of the T.B. location employees actually served older, COLDER food, and often prepared the items with substandard ingredients or haphazardly throwing them together, resulty in a soggy, dishelveled, often inedible mess- AFTER  putting in a special request to prepare it fresh,  the way I remembered most restaurants to be growing up, when eating out was a treat, just as it has become once again. Although I use the term "treat" lightly, since only ONE of 10 hit all the marks!!

And 2 others were just slightly redeemed when they offered to remake what was arguably the absolute worst delivery of what had been my favorite yearly treat of salty, cheesy goodness of fresh, hot, perfectly seasoned, slightly crispy outside, fluffy inside potato indulgence, dunked in wonderfully hot, drippy nacho cheese dunking sauce!

The remade fries at those two did eventually meet my expectations of receiving hot, fresh and crispy seasoned fries with a small condiment cup portion of perfectly tempered cheese sauce, while the other food items consistantly were served old, cold, often soggy, and barely edible!

So, THANK YOU Newtown Road TacoBell, for finally giving me the perfect meal to end my "local tour" to remind me what eating fast food out used to be like, back when employees cared about their customers, their jobs, and the products they served, and almost anyone could scrape together enough coins from under the sofa cushions or car floor and still get something yummy and satisfying to eat! üòãü•§üåÆü•ôüçüüåØ

title: MP Island Caf√©
address: 923 Glenrock Rd, Norfolk, VA 23502
text:
MP Island Caf√©, tucked away near Military Highway, is a true local gem that offers a delightful escape from the everyday, easily earning it a strong four-star rating. This is the place to go when you're craving authentic Caribbean and Filipino flavors, served up with genuine warmth.
The food here is consistently excellent. Their oxtail is a must-try ‚Äì tender, fall-off-the-bone, and swimming in a rich, deeply flavorful sauce. The jerk chicken packs a perfect punch of spice and smoky char, and their lumpia are crispy, savory bites of heaven. What truly stands out is the authenticity; each dish tastes like it's been lovingly prepared with traditional recipes and fresh ingredients. They also offer a fantastic variety, so there‚Äôs always something new and exciting to try, whether you‚Äôre in the mood for a hearty curry or a lighter seafood dish.
The atmosphere is laid-back and welcoming. It's not a fancy place, but it's clean, comfortable, and has a no-frills charm that makes you feel right at home. It‚Äôs the kind of spot where you can relax and truly enjoy your meal. The staff are also a huge part of the appeal ‚Äì friendly, attentive, and always happy to guide you through the menu if you're new to the cuisine.
While MP Island Caf√© is fantastic, it doesn't quite hit five stars due to a couple of minor points. Given its popularity, seating can sometimes be a bit limited, especially during peak lunch or dinner rushes. Also, because everything is made fresh, there can sometimes be a bit of a wait for your food, though it's always well worth it.
Despite these minor considerations, MP Island Caf√© is a fantastic culinary find near Military Highway. It's a vibrant, flavorful, and incredibly satisfying experience that will transport your taste buds straight to the islands. Highly recommended for anyone looking for delicious, authentic Caribbean and Filipino food in Norfolk.

text: A horrible experience, being that it was our first time there, we asked to sit at the table close to the bar. The waiter said OK, so we headed over. As we sat there and waited, there were tables next to us getting service and no one had yet come to our table. Then a lady walks up and tells us that we had to be seated, which we explained that we were, and then we were told that we were not seated and that our table needed to be turned on. All of that happened in 10 minutes. As we were ordering, I asked for the crab balls and boom shrimp, which took forever to come out. In fact, my wife‚Äôs pasta dish came out before the shrimp, which was weird. Upon tasting her pasta, it tasted like it came straight out of a box and the toast was freezer burnt. Halfway through her dish, the shrimp I ordered arrived, and because it was overcooked It was extremely tough, like chicken, so I told the waiter there was no way I could eat it. Irritated by the awful experience, I asked for the check and, on top of the tasteless experience, the tab was $110, which we felt that we were overcharged, but we paid it and would never come back. I‚Äôm at liberty to believe that people tolerate this food because they are usually under the influence of alcohol. If anyone plans to ever go to this place, eat before you go.

title: MP Island Caf√©
address: 923 Glenrock Rd, Norfolk, VA 23502
text:
It had been almost a year since my last visit because I live in NC, but I have to bring my mom here anytime we are in VA. My Jamaican mother has a discerning palate, and this is the only Caribbean food that passes her tests. She also likes to hit up the grocery section for items she can't find locally.

We were blessed to arrive at a time when there was hardly a line. Throughout years of patronage, we have waited in a long line at every location of this restaurant. Don't get me wrong, the food is worth the wait, and the line is part of the experience, but it was so nice to be able to order right away. I immediately noticed some items available on the hot bar like ackee and saltfish - I hadn't seen that offered before. I'd also never seen every pattie variety available at once. I was happy to be able to have the veggie and the spinach and cheese as vegetarian options.

The staff was wonderful. They were patient with my mother who still is never ready to order when it's her turnüòÖ. The staff also graciously navigated another issue when I attempted to pay for our food. I hadn't noticed my mom ordering another entree and changing the size of her plates. The staff informed me discreetly, easily figured the difference, and quickly sorted everything out.

We then went to the grocery side where my mom idly browsed the aisles. We were greeted by a very nice young man who was stocking shelves. This same young man was our cashier and he was so polite and kind and helpful. He took his time with my mom's items and loaded bags into her cart. I was so impressed, he was clearly raised very well. I wish I got his name because he deserves to be recognized. Please let him know he is doing an excellent job and I wish him well in life. It is so nice to encounter truly kind people, especially when they are young.

Anyway, I digress, the food was excellent. I brought a large oxtail dinner home for my husband, and he cleaned the plate. My hot patties were delicious, and I also purchased the unbaked, frozen versions of them from the grocery. I also stocked up on hot sauce and snacks. Best visit so far.

text:
The staff here is utterly incompetent. Just go somewhere else.

They ignored my family at the counter. We waited until we gave up and used the kiosk. This, despite having made eye contact several times with numerous associates.

They were quick to help the next group that didn't look like us. I feel like we were discriminated against.

Our order was wrong. Several items were made incorrectly. The associate argued that point. When they remade those items, they were rolling their eyes, being rough with the food, and making rude comments to their co-worker while they laughed about it.

I'm really at a loss here.  I can't recall ever having such an unbelievably bad experience just trying to grab dinner for the kids.

Mind you that our little ones are two and four and the employees were so disrespectful in front of them.

I will absolutely not be returning to this location. I've been living in Hampton Roads for 18 years. This area is my home, and this "restaurant" has forfeited a lifetime of business from my family.

As much as I've shared, it barely begins to cover how disappointed and upset we were having wasted our time and money here.

Like I started with.. .

Just go somewhere else.

title: Chinatown restaurant
address: 4848 Virginia Beach Blvd #11, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text:
So I'm always worried about new Chinese delivery because they are notoriously famous for no descriptions or photos. I totally understand why independent owners struggle with making that a priority financially. I was impressed with the portion sizes and the food came super hot which for delivery is impressive. The prices were some of the lowest which I loved.
My items:
1. Pork Egg Fu Young. Came with 3 decent sized omelets, white rice, and a generous portion of gravy. The gravy was thick and very flavorful. It was rich and delicious. This is how I rate Chinese food and for this I'd give it a 5 out of 5.
2. Pork Lo Mein. A quart size was packed full. The sauce was tasty and the pork was pretty tender. Not a huge amount of pork but for the price I was OK with it.
3. Smoked Sausage and Fried Rice. The sausage was generous and tasted great. A little char from the frying which made it even better. The rice wasn't any traditional fried rice (there was no brown color from a soy sauce). It has no flavor in my opinion but I ordered extra gravy and I added this which made it so much better.
4. Fried scallops. Came golden brown. The scallops are from frozen but really sweet and a great crispy coating. In the picture I added flaky garlic salt because everything fried needs it in my opinion.
5. The fried chicken potstickers were super small but tasted great. I got them free from an advertisement so I can't complain!  The dumpling sauce was awesome!
I will definitely be ordering from there again!
If you're on the fence give it a try for sure.

title: Ibis Cuisine Restaurant
address: 928 Diamond Springs Rd, Virginia Beach, VA 23455
text:
Had dinner Friday at Ibis - EXCELLENT in every way- service, atmosphere, quality and quantity of the entr√©e and courtesy and friendliness of the staff. They gave me a great table, despite not having a reservation and it only got better from there.
I had the short ribs - AMAZING is all I can say. Really didn't need a knife as the meat fell of the bone and was covered with a wine reduction sauce that was fabulous. In addition,the gouda dish accompanying the ribs gave a whole new meaning to "mac and cheese"!
I also ordered a their side salad. It was very fresh and arranged so nicely that I almost hated to ruin it by eating - Ha!

All-in-all, Ibis is a REAL GEM. So Glad I discovered it and will definitely be returning!

We proceeded to wait there for over 20 minutes for our food, which they apparently gave away to another person in the drive-through.  Workers were also rude to my wife when she went inside to figure out what was going on.  They then told us it was our fault we went to the wrong window (even though I went to the window I was told to go to), never apologized for our food being delayed, and then couldn‚Äôt even give us the correct order at the end (I had to ask twice for our drinks), and they were out of Coke after all this. text: This has become my go to pizza place. I live in the neighborhood so it‚Äôs real easy to get to. We always order an 18 inch pepperoni pizza with extra cheese. The consistent inconsistencies is making me feel it‚Äôs time to search for another pizza place sadly.

title: Sal‚Äôs NY Slice Pizzeria
address: 5604 Princess Anne Rd, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text:
Sal‚Äôs NY Slice Pizzeria at 5604 Princess Anne Rd

It was early Sunday in the afternoon and this pizza place caught my eye while driving by.
I figured why not get a pizza slice.
I was welcomed with a clean and neat interior with simple chairs and tables with blue, well designed, covers and a friendly woman working the register.
After asking for a menu, I saw they offered a lot more than your popular Italian pie.
So, I didn't ask for a slice. I got the Fettuccine Alfredo with shrimp and broccoli instead.
My salad that it came with was fresh complete with red onions, green peppers, croutons, and crisp lettuce which was not at all soggy. Of course, I had to have ranch with it.
The Alfredo pasta was almost authentically perfect with the sauce made from parmesan according to the nice woman. I added more parmesan from the shaker which contributed a more powdered texture to my meal. The sauce was rich and creamy. The shrimp was tender and the broccoli added a soft crunch. I liked it! You can tell the meal had this homemade charm and it tasted like it. It was quite good!
The soft bread was delicious with a punch of garlic and butter but not too overwhelming. It was not brittle or dry and it was tasty!
Overall, a nice charming takeout or sit down place where you can enjoy a delightful meal guaranteed to leave you full!

text:
The worst pizza I've had in a long time.  Stopped here for lunch. The place being entirely empty should have been a red flag, but we were hungry and we were already here. The pizza was incredibly bland. Total lack of flavor.  The sauce reminded me of those pizzas we were served in the middle school cafeteria. The cheese was very low quality. The crust had zero taste, although it was at least cooked right.  The toppings didn't taste fresh at all.  If you told me this pizza was frozen before being cooked, I would believe you.  We each ate one slice and left hungry.  It simply wasn't worth eating, even after paying $30 for it.

The owner responded, claiming that we must have been reviewing the wrong location.  I can assure you this is the location that we visited.  It's right between a billiards place and Dunkin.  There is a huge werewolf on display inside of the restaurant.

address: 928 Diamond Springs Rd, Virginia Beach, VA 23455
text:
Ordered through door dash on 3/30. They offered a special of wings, a pizza, and some garlic knots but it wouldn‚Äôt allow me to pick the toppings on the pizza or the flavor of wings so I figured I‚Äôd just call the place and talk to them about it. Before I could call them a woman working that day called me and lectured me about how I shouldn‚Äôt be ordering through door dash because they charge more and next time I need to call them directly. She said if she hadn‚Äôt been working they would have just made everything plain and not bothered calling to check if that‚Äôs what I wanted. Well, there won‚Äôt be a next time. I had no idea this place existed except for through door dash, nor did I have any idea they would deliver to me. As far as I know, your business has to volunteer to be on door dash so why am I being scolded for using it? I understand there were some technical difficulties but that should be taken up with DoorDash, not me.

I still ordered the food regardless. I asked for garlic park wings and they tasted very lemony. I threw them out. The garlic knots were pretty dry and the pizza was average. I‚Äôm happier ordering dominos

text:
Best pizza in Virginia Beach. I know a lot of people are ordering through apps now but small local owned restaurants like this can really use families coming in and sitting down like they used to. In addition, they have the best Christmas treats around. You have to order them way ahead of time.
Edit: while the quality of the food has not changed, as they try to update and use delivery services or deliver themselves there has been a problem on multiple occasions. Unfortunately, we have ordered twice and both times they was delivered early . Last evening, 11/21/25, the order for delivery was for 6:00 to 6:15 p.m. showed up an hour early, and was ice cold. I called the restaurant, they offered no solution. The big issue for me is not paying attention to order details and I tipped well. Just as though I were in the restaurant.

I will update if somebody reaches out to me and makes it right.

Visited interlude this past Mothers Day for breakfast. The food was awesome but my waitress *Grace delivered the food and the check about 30 secs later.  I was in a state of shock but continued to watch other tables in my area to see maybe if the same thing was happening. Sad to say it wasn't. Giving her the benefit of the doubt , maybe her shift was ending early and she forgot to mention it or maybe she was changing areas in the restaurant all of which proved to not be true. We ate for another 30 minutes or so giving plenty of time to enjoy the food and see if she'd ask about the bill. That did not happen. I paid leaving $0 tip of course and took a picture of the receipt and was sure to use my Amex Gold Business card due to the ease of which I could dispute and track if a tip would be added afterwards. Sorry to say that's indeed what happened. Grace added a little over $4 bucks for a $41 dollar meal. Its not $ of course , the principal. Ive since disputed and AMEX is on the case. Very very unfortunate but I refuse to be taken advantage of and be made to feel like a 2nd class citizen.

title: McDonald's (Newtown Rd)
address: 745 Newtown Rd, Norfolk, VA 23502
text:
NOW SERVING PREFERENTIAL TREATMENT FOR NON-BLACKS AT THIS LOCATION - A.K.A DISCRIMINATION!
I came to this establishment to pick up an order for someone, and when I entered, there wasn't a team member at the register. On the other side of the counter was a Caucasian female with her two adolescent children. We were both waiting to be served. The Caucasian woman, in her impatience, elevated her tone so the team members in the kitchen could hear and asked "can we get some help over here?" Another Caucasian female with a short, blonde hair cut, dressed in all black walked out and asked the annoyed woman with two children what she needed. I stood at the pickup counter and waited patiently to be recognized, and instead, the white team member refused to acknowledge me. So I kindly said as she was passing, "excuse me, I'm here to pick up and order for [insert name here]." She quickly interjected as I was talking and replied, "it will be out when it's ready," then walked away. I immediately left the store and canceled the order. NOT TODAY SATAN! Her real irritation was toward the Caucasian female with two adolescent children, but instead she chose to use me as target practice - the kind African American woman who spoke to her with RESPECT! You must be out of your mind to think that I would accept that projection. I didn't deserve the disrespect, but the white woman with two kids surely did. Why did she think it was remotely acceptable to be rude to me? Two women are in front of her: one white, one black. One rude, one respectful, and yet she targeted the black, respectful one. Call it racist, call it discriminatory, call it a bad day, call it whatever you want! I call it disgusting and unacceptable. If you are African American, I urge you NOT to spend your dollars and cents here. They do not treat black people like they are worthy of common courtesy. You were warned!

The cheese was ooey-gooey goodness and blended well with the sausage and pepperoni. It also came with some marinara for dipping. I ate half while we were there and took the other half to go. We will definitely be ordering from here again in the future. Thanks for a great meal!

text:
The place was really good. I come to this little shopping center often because there are a lot of great places in here and it's primarily for the local crowd in Virginia Beach. I showed up with a friend for lunch and we both got the 2 slice lunch special. They had some various other lunch specials as well, but I was pretty set on those pizzas. You can put one topping on each of the pizzas if you want or you can just get cheese.
The pizza is thin crust and was definitely pretty good. It reminded me of a very similar style to NYC pizza and I prefer that style myself. We also got the garlic knots and they were delicious. It's like they put a whole loaf in the oven and just infused it with garlic flavor! The portions for that were large! Maybe include a little more marinara sauce for the next time.

address: 5604 Princess Anne Rd, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text:
First time at Sal's. Decent pizza, I wish all non-pork pepperoni was this good. All the meats are pork free. I had one slice,  $4. It was decent, with good flavor. Sauce had a nice tang, and the cheese was okay. Not as good as the Benny's chain and perhaps just a bit under Delvecchio's, but a decent slice. Foldable.

The service was very nice. People are terrific here, very helpful, and kind. The standard slice condiments were there, and I availed myself off the cheese, cracked red pepper flakes, and a touch of garlic.

The dining room was clean and neat with a giant monster dominating the room. I don't know why it's there, but I did enjoy its presence.

I would go back. Nice people, lower price point. Better than Marco's across the street, but only just better.

Go visit,  you won't regret it.

address: 5604 Princess Anne Rd, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text:
I wish I could rate Sal's NY Pizzeria located @ 5604 Princess Anne Road 10 stars!
Where do I start?
#1: The customer service at this location is the best I've experienced at any pizzeria in Virginia Beach. That includes all of their employees!
#2: They did an excellent job of helping me organize a next day pickup for a huge pizza party! Not only were they punctual, but all of my items were hot & ready prior to the scheduled pickup time!
#3: I absolutely LOVED their meat selection being 100% pork free! Their beef pepperoni and beef+Turkey sausage had better flavor than their pork counterparts.
#4: I loved their variety of pizza combinations and flavors. It's unlike anything I've ever seen! You can do any combination of half & half pizzas even if they're 2 different sauces.
