title: Big Apple Pizzeria
address: 928 Diamond Springs Rd, Virginia Beach, VA 23455
text:
By far the Best Pizzaria that I have visited in Virginia Beach or anywhere in Years.
The Pizza was cooked to perfection with no flop, the way I love my slices.
The Chicken Parmigiana hero was to absolutely die for.
Perfect combination and merge of chicken, sauce and cheese.

A lot of Restaurant's claim and have NY Pizza in the store name as a gimmick to get people into the door only to be let down.
I can assure you as a 35+ year resident of Long Island NY that lives here now, You Will Not Be Let Down.
100% Quality and 10 out of 10 in my eyes.

text:
I used to love this location and would literally drive out of my way to come here, but lately it‚Äôs been awful, stale old food, and order messed up every single time.
I placed my order, drove up to the window, they said they‚Äôre having register issues and wanted me to wait. That‚Äôs not their fault. However, I watched my food sit at the windowsill for the full 25 minutes, and the manager looked me dead in the face and STILL tried to hand it out to me. I asked her nicely to please remake my entire order.. no reason I should have to eat that. She was nice about it, but why did she try to give it to me in the first place? I pull to the third window to wait for my food. The manager with the short ginger hair is always so rude and always has an attitude, and she was rude at this pickup window as well. Mad at me because I don‚Äôt want rock solid food.. Half of my order was missing! So I had no choice but to go inside. With customer service here these days, when you go inside the building, you get fully neglected. Looked at 10 times but nobody asks you if you need help. And I‚Äôm the most understanding when it comes to mistakes, but it seems to be the same mistakes every time. The time before this, they forgot my mcchicken, I went in, and the manager with the long brown hair literally grabbed an old mcchicken out of the till; walked it back to the kitchen yelling ‚Äúcan you add pickles to this??‚Äù right in front of me.. there‚Äôs absolutely no shame. Today I decided to go for breakfast and they gave me a muffin that was hard as a rock and tasted like it‚Äôs been sitting out all morning. Old food is the trend here. I‚Äôve given them enough chances and I‚Äôm sick of it. No more.

title: Big Apple Pizzeria
address: 928 Diamond Springs Rd, Virginia Beach, VA 23455
text:
I decided to try this place after finding their pamphlet in the mail.  I've had some poorly prepared food before, but this place has successfully topped them all.  Not only was our food poorly made and overcooked, all the ingredients used in our meals tasted exceptionally cheap.

My son got the NY Buffalo Chicken wrap and couldn't finish it.  He complained that the chicken was mushy, the sauce was really salty, and the wrap was dry without the ranch dipping sauce.  I took a bite and can confirm everything he said was true.  Despite the salty flavor and mushy texture, it was at least edible.

I got the stuff shells.  It was a lesson and a reminder to never order this unless you can confirm the expertise of the chef.  It looked edible, but I was disappointed after cutting into it.  The mozzarella cheese they use was probably the cheapest you can buy and was so baked on that it was like cutting into rubber.  I'm assuming the shells were stuffed with Ricotta cheese, but it was so dry, flavorless, and gritty that I couldn't really tell what it was.  I got halfway through the meal, and couldn't stomach the rest.

My wife got the Gyro.  There was so much grease in it that it actually broke the Tzatziki sauce and turned the pita into mush.  She had thrown it away before I could snap a picture of it, and I wasn't about to fish it out of the garbage.  She tried to eat it, but the mushy pita bread and nasty broken sauce were deal breakers for her.

Normally, I give a place a few tries even after a bad experience.  But, to fail so completely from start to finish on every item in my order is inexcusable and undeserving of future patronage.

text: I visited this Sakura for the first time because it‚Äôs in the neighborhood that I just moved to. It wasn‚Äôt deep fried and I took the shrimp tempura back into the restaurant, and I politely asked the staff to deep fry it it tasted u cooked. the lady who worked there took it to the kitchen however, the man who work behind the counter who‚Äôs picture Ihave attached. This young man started cursing at me and told me if I didn‚Äôt like it for me to get out and threatened to Throw me out .there was approximately six or seven other customers in the restaurant at the time they were all Caucasian. I believe that because I was a black African-American female, the man behind the counter, thought it was OK for him to curse me out and speak to me in a disrespectful manner. Of course, I put him in his place and let him know that I‚Äôm a retired officer, and my money was given back to me. I felt that this was a racist move and that I wouldn‚Äôt recommend other customers of color to visit this restaurant. From now on, I‚Äôll drive to the other Sakura restaurant on Lynnhaven Parkway because the food is good the atmosphere is good and the customer service is excellent. title: Sakura Japanese Restaurant
address: 4716 Virginia Beach Blvd, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text:
I wish I could give a NEGATIVIE 5-star review.  Customer Service is awful. Have been to the one Shore Dr and Hampton Rd, and it‚Äôs night and day. PLEASE do not go to this place.

I wanted to take my son out for some father-son time. We arrived and seated right after another customer and was given the menu and took our drink orders. After 15 or so minutes, we are still waiting to place our order while the customer who came in right before us were able to place their orders and receive their food. I literally had to get up and walk to the front and ask if someone could please take our order. Finally, he came over to take our orders for miso soup, rolls, and sushi. After over 30 mins, our soup came. I made a statement ‚Äúlooks like you guys are busy tonight.‚Äù There are only 2 other tables occupied. I told him when he bring our food out if he could please bring our check out also. Instead of ‚Äúsorry for the delay‚Äù, he got super defensive and said if I don‚Äôt like the service, I can leave. I did not feed into his rude comments/gesture and said, "Please bring our food out when you can." He responded ‚Äúyou leave now‚Äù As embarrassed as I was, I asked to speak to the manager, and he pulled out a chair and sat down and said," What do you want? " I asked if he was the manager, and he kept going on. My son and I got up and left.

I've never been kicked out of a restaurant before, especially with my son. This place customer service has the most horrific experience. They give a bad name to the restaurant name ‚ÄúSurka‚Äù and should change their name. Will never go back here ever again even if they give out food for free. Customers are aware.

title: Sakura Japanese Restaurant

text: The before and after should speak for itself. Out of pure curiosity I stopped here during a walk. Out of loads of sushi places I have visited, their rice has a proper lightly roasted taste to it. This is rare to find, the rice temperature is also matched to the dish you order. That said, fish is fresh but the cook excels in chicken based dishes. The dish shown above is their Chicken teriyaki. All featured items shown are not muffled, each pronounces their unique flavors while still working alongside the sauces. Nothing I tasted is overwhelming and plays well together. Also! This place is quiet! Even on a Friday, holiday weekend. Mainly visited by reoccurring locals, you can actually sit and enjoy your meal here without being pressured to eat quickly. Stay, enjoy, and love food, this is a proper place to enjoy.

title: Subway
address: 665 Newtown Rd #105, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text:
As I stepped into the welcoming ambiance of the Subway on Fifth Avenue, the staff's delightful demeanor promised an extraordinary culinary experience. The sandwich at hand‚Äîa bold meld of tuna and pepperoni, enlivened by sharp jalape√±os and smoothed over with creamy mayonnaise, all encased in an Italian herb and cheese bread‚Äîwas a gastronomic saga in itself. The ensemble of flavors was impeccably balanced, with each ingredient playing its part to elevate the simple sandwich into a memorable meal.

This creation was a vivid testament to Subway's culinary artistry, challenging and comforting the palate in equal measure. The passionate recommendations from the engaging staff only enhanced the experience, embodying the spirit that great culinary art can indeed emerge from the most unexpected places. As Anton Ego would appreciate, this was not just a sandwich; it was a small, sublime slice of life served with a smile.

text:
Absolutely the worst restaurant experience I‚Äôve had in a long time.

Our group was accused of damaging equipment after their own server placed a water dispenser too close to the edge of the table. When someone stood up, it accidentally fell. Only two people in our group were drinking‚Äîand it wasn‚Äôt even one of them who knocked it over. Water went everywhere, and we immediately informed our server.

They sent someone in to clean it, but she just spread the water around the small room, soaking a cord that was already lying across the floor when we first arrived. Shortly after, the manager stormed in and accused us of breaking a ‚Äú$2,000 piece of equipment.‚Äù I tried to calmly explain what had happened, but she completely ignored me and walked out.

I had to repeatedly ask for someone to come back and explain the situation. When she finally returned, she told us we had to leave immediately‚Äîbut that she ‚Äúwouldn‚Äôt charge us‚Äù for the equipment. When I asked her to prove it was broken, she said she couldn‚Äôt because the microphone stand it supposedly connected to was damaged. Laughable.

They made us leave 20 minutes early and still charged us the full hourly room fee. The waitress and other staff were kind until the manager got involved. After that, their attitude flipped and they became incredibly rude. I‚Äôm truly appalled at the way we were treated. Avoid this place.

text:
So, the reviews seem mixed. Having ordered from them, I feel like they deserve an objective review. My biggest issue was that it took 50 minutes to get food delivered, restaurant was 4 min from my hotel, on a Tuesday night. It was irritating, but things happen. I did order 20min before delivery cutoff

First item, egg drop wonton soup. This item was EXCELLENT, some of the best I've had from a strip mall Chinese place. Cooked perfectly, wontons were nice, and three of them in a pint of soup.  Broth was delicious, thick and rich. ‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê

Egg Roll, basic, garden variety. Needed a few more minutes to cook. Not bad, not great. ‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê

Shrimp Lo Mein, it was good, nice taste, not too dry, not too saucy. Noodles weren't soggy, and veggies had a little crunch to them, even tho l had to microwave them to reheat. Could have used a few more shrimp, but even the shrimp were cooked right, not tough and overcooked.
‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê

So, to review, the food was satisfying , filling, and good. I would order from them again, if I were local. More of a lunch place for me. I'd think it's the sort of place that if you're a regular and pickup your own food, it's probably a much better experience.

title: Volcano Sushi, Grill, Bar& karaoke (Town Center)
address: 4830 Virginia Beach Blvd, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text: A group of 12+ attempted to dine in Wednesday evening, June 25th. The temperature inside was a sweltering 83 degrees. We had two servers, James and Mariah. James provided great service and tried his best to accommodate our large party, even had ice waters delivered to the table in advance. Unfortunately the incredibly warm temperature and the overwhelming amount of gnats flying around every table made it very difficult to have an enjoyable evening. Drinks from the bar took 25 minutes to obtain even though our group and another 2 person party were the only ones present. We requested to speak with the a manager after Mariah got audibly irritated with a few members of our group but the manager never showed, even after asking for them 3 times. Finally we were told the manager was on the phone with the General Manager. In short, we ended up not dining at Volcano and likely won't return. 0/10 would NOT recommend.

title: Volcano Sushi, Grill, Bar& karaoke (Town Center)
address: 4830 Virginia Beach Blvd, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text:
Review: 1/5 Stars
We recently visited Volcano with a group of friends from work, eager to have a great time as we‚Äôve enjoyed karaoke nights before at another spot. Unfortunately, our experience here was disappointing from the start.
We were excited by the setup, which included a huge selection of songs and the ability to use YouTube, but the service was completely unacceptable. Upon arrival, we waited at the bar to order drinks while our room was being set up, but no one attended to us. After finally ordering, it took over 45 minutes to get our first round of drinks. I also ordered an appetizer, but it didn‚Äôt arrive until the very last plate of food, as it was apparently forgotten by the kitchen staff. The waitress was quick to assure us it wasn‚Äôt her fault but didn‚Äôt take responsibility for the delay.
To make matters worse, while one of my friends was singing, the manager came in and turned down the microphones so low that we couldn‚Äôt hear anything. We mentioned this to the staff and hoped they‚Äôd adjust the volume, but the response was unsatisfactory. Instead, the music became unbearably loud, making it nearly impossible to enjoy the karaoke experience.
Throughout the night, the staff was inattentive and, frankly, rude. It was clear they were not interested in making sure we had a good time. This place could have so much potential, but I wouldn't recommend it to anyone. Fortunately, I won‚Äôt be coming back or bringing anyone here again.

title: Volcano Sushi, Grill, Bar& karaoke (Town Center)
address: 4830 Virginia Beach Blvd, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text:
I was excited to try out this karaoke venue, especially given my appreciation for Japanese culture. The atmosphere initially seemed high-tech and promising, and I appreciated the convenience of using YouTube for song selection. However, the service was some of the worst I‚Äôve experienced at any establishment.

Despite my friends ordering drinks, they waited 45 minutes without receiving them. The staff frequently disrupted our experience‚Äîone employee even interrupted my performance mid-song, speaking over me as I continued singing. At another point, the microphones were abruptly turned off with no explanation. For a paying customer, this level of service was unacceptable.

Overall, while the concept and setup had potential, the unprofessional and inattentive staff completely undermined the experience. I cannot recommend this venue unless serious improvements are made.

text: I arrived and ordered my food BEFORE the crowd came in. There seemed to be enough wait staff even after the crowd arrived. I've worked in the restaurant industry for many years, so I have very little sympathy if a restaurant can't do it right. With that being said, this has always been a rule in the restaurant world: If a customer does not order any appetizers, then their food needs to be all cooked relatively the same time and come out the relatively same time! If you did not know this, then you were poorly trained. It should never be that a dish comes out, then 20 minutes later, the second dish comes out; then 15 minutes later, the third dish comes out.

title: Jade Villa Chinese Restaurant
address: 353 Independence Blvd, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text:
A Portal to Authentic Chinese Cuisine Hiding in Plain Sight
For years, I treated Jade Villa as my go-to for fantastic, American-style Chinese food. Their General Tso's is top-tier, the beef and broccoli is always fresh and crisp, and the service is consistently warm and welcoming. It has always been a reliable five-star spot in my book for just that. But a recent visit transformed my entire understanding of this neighborhood gem.
During a conversation with one of the incredibly friendly owners, I mentioned my travels in Asia and my love for the cuisine there. A smile spread across their face, and they returned to the table with a different menu, one not typically handed to every customer. This was the key to a completely different world. This "secret" menu was filled with dishes you'd find on a family's table in Hong Kong or a bustling eatery in Guangzhou ‚Äì items that might seem "weird" to some, but are the heart and soul of authentic Chinese cooking.
We decided to be adventurous and dive in. We ordered the braised chicken feet in black bean sauce, something I hadn't enjoyed since a trip abroad. They were phenomenal‚Äîtender, gelatinous, and packed with savory flavor. We also tried the salt and pepper squid, which was perfectly crispy without being greasy, and a soul-warming bowl of century egg and pork congee that was the ultimate comfort food. It was like being transported thousands of miles away.
What makes Jade Villa truly exceptional is that they masterfully cater to two different worlds. They execute the American Chinese classics with a freshness and quality that is hard to beat, while also offering a genuine taste of Asia for those willing to ask. The staff is more than happy to guide you through the traditional menu with pride. If you think you know Jade Villa, I urge you to ask about their other menu. You'll discover it's not just a great Chinese restaurant; it's a culinary passport. An absolute five-star treasure!

So I asked her to explain the menu specials, because I had the menu in front of me, and she got frustrated. She put the phone down and came back asking again what do you want? I was upset. I said well I need more info about your menu so I can tell you and she said well call me back when you know what you want. And actually hung up on me. I was appalled. So I called back and she answered the same as before. I said yes I just called, and she says I know who you are what you want?! I still made my order nonetheless and she got my order right and wrong. A simple chicken and white rice was turned into a chicken with fried rice and my daughter hates fried rice and that was her meal I had purchased for her. I actually was going to go to the restaurant and see who she was because her attitude SUCKED so bad If I want food I hesitate and deliberate for hours with my husband before we order. The guys are nice but the women there suck. They lack customer service skills. She shouldn't answer their phones AT ALL. THEY WILL LOSE BUSINESS BEHIND HER RUDE TAIL !! the food is pretty good for the most part though. But who wants to go thru ignorance to eat??!! Word of advice for them: FIRE HER TAIL!!

text:
I had an amazing experience at Volcano Sushi, Grill, Bar & Karaoke in Town Center! From start to finish, everything was top notch. I started with the Flaming Volcano drink, which was not only a spectacle but also deliciously smooth with just the right amount of kick.

For dinner, we went all out with the Grand Volcano Carnival, where you get to choose five special rolls. Every single one was incredible! The Yaming Yaming had a perfect balance of flavors, the Tiger Roll was fresh and flavorful, the Golden Lobster was rich and indulgent, the Jaguar Roll had a nice spicy kick, and the Phoenix Roll was an absolute standout.

The atmosphere was lively and fun, and the service was fantastic. Whether you‚Äôre here for sushi, drinks, or a night of karaoke, this place delivers. I‚Äôll definitely be back!

text:
It is a very cool place with a great atmosphere. Moving pictures take up an entire wall with scenes from Japan. Very beautiful.

The sushi (avocado and sweet potato for me since I'm vegan) was very good. The kitchen food was not as good. The noodles had excessive sesame oil. They have no vegan salad dressings and could only offer me vinegar. They used soft tofu instead of firm for the tofu teriyaki.

The server was friendly,  informative, and helpful.  However,  no one ever removed a dirty dish from our table.  We kept stacking them up on the end of our table when we were done with them. They were still there when we left after paying our bill and finishing our drinks.

This place has private karaoke rooms that are soundproof and rented by the hour. We will come back and try that!

title: Jade Villa Chinese Restaurant
address: 353 Independence Blvd, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text: A great place to try the real deal Chinese food.  This place is definitely for foodies. Protip: Order off of the red menu, not the white menu.  While this place closed last year, it has since reopened under new management but has not lost a step.  They've modernized the place with a new floor, new ceiling tiles, new walls.  The food tastes just the same, excellent.  If you want beef and broccoli or shrimp lo mein, go to any other place, although you can get those items if you want.  They also do dim sum on Sundays especially.  The staff are polite and professional.  They are following current respiratory hygiene guidelines.  Recommended.

address: 676 N Witchduck Rd, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text:
I go to this place multiple times a year, food is always great, staff is nice, I noticed management or ownership has changed, but they still serve good food.
The reason I am giving 3 star, is the lady in the kitchen, which is open, cooks with her hair not covered, that is a BIG NO in the restaurant world, if a piece of hair fall into food that is a disaster.
Second the atmosphere is not great and place smelled moldy like an old motel with poor look, owner needs to put some $ to renovate. These two things shut me down and made me not enjoy my meal as I used to, I will unlikely go back.

title: Mazari Kebab & More
address: 676 N Witchduck Rd, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text:
It was takeout so I couldn‚Äôt rate the service and atmosphere but the restaurant looks clean and good when I went to pick it up.
But the food is amazing, I had so much in my plate (chicken kebab platter) with rice and two sides and they were not greasy or not the kind of food that makes you feel guilty from eating. Chicken seasoning was on point, kabuli rice was good I had fries and steamed vege with it. 100 percent would definitely come back.
My husband got the kobida gyro with chickpeas and tomato and cucumber salad as add ons. He loved all of them. I only got pix of my husband‚Äôs order cos I was hungry.

Updated:
I did pick up order again and this time I had lamb chop platter. I recommend the eggplant as a side as it is flavorful. Good portion of lamb chops and very tender. We also ordered falafel.
My recommendations
-lamb chop platter
-chicken kebab platter
- gyro (beef and lamb are good)
- eggplant as a side

title: Volcano Sushi, Grill, Bar& karaoke (Town Center)
address: 4830 Virginia Beach Blvd, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text:
I recently visited Volcano Sushi, Grill, Bar & Karaoke, and had an amazing experience from start to finish. Our waitress, Jasmine, made the evening even better with her friendly and attentive service. She was personable, checked in regularly, and ensured everything was just right‚Äîwithout ever being overbearing.

The food was top-notch. We started with some delicious appetizers that set the tone for the meal‚Äîeverything was fresh, flavorful, and beautifully presented. The grilled items were cooked to perfection. Each dish felt carefully prepared and really elevated the dining experience.

The karaoke bar was lively and in full swing while we dined, adding an extra fun vibe to the atmosphere. Though I didn‚Äôt take part in the karaoke this time, the energy in the room was contagious. I‚Äôm already planning my next visit and, who knows, maybe I‚Äôll give a song or two a try!

Overall, Volcano Sushi, Grill, Bar & Karaoke exceeded my expectations, and I‚Äôm excited to return. Great food, great service, and a lively ambiance make it a spot worth coming back to.

title: Jade Villa Chinese Restaurant
address: 353 Independence Blvd, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text:
I had high expectations for this restaurant based on the reviews, but I was very let down by both the service and the food.
When me and my family arrived, it took five minutes for the waitress to seat us. I would‚Äôve understood if they were busy, but there were only two other tables occupied and they already had their food. After we sat down, we waited another five minutes for the waitress to ask us what we wanted to drink, just for her to take another couple of minutes to give them to us. Then after waiting almost 20 minutes, we had to flag down another waiter because our waitress forgot about us. It also took a long time for them to bring utensils and plates that we needed.
We ordered the creamy corn soup and the hot and sour soup for the appetizer. Both appetizers were flavorless.
For the entree, we ordered the hunan shrimp, fried rice, pepper steak, and pork and shrimp shumai. The hunan shrimp and the pepper steak were ok, but the fried rice was underseasoned. As for the pork and shrimp shumai, it had an odd taste and it lacked flavor and sauce. I am highly disappointed

title: Jade Villa Chinese Restaurant
address: 353 Independence Blvd, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text:
A good friend recommended this place, but I will tell him that he doesn't need to come again.
Our family of 5 arrived at about 7pm on July 2nd. We stood by the service counter for several minutes and no one paid attention to us. It was not very busy, and there were several empty tables. There were waiters who saw us, but they didn't say a word, as if they didn't see us. And there was a gentleman who stood and looked forward all the time.
I understand that different positions have different service scopes, but you can at least say hello or wait a moment. But there was no one.

Because we don't want to waste our time in a place with such terrible service attitude. So after standing there for a few minutes, we decided to leave. I don't think this restaurant is worth coming to, at least on this day.

text: This is the best Chinese food I have ever had.  We have lived in several places, and of course, try the Chinese food when we're in other cities, but nothing is as good as Hong Kong House. text:
Not the same, but decent for take out.

Used to love this place(5 or so years ago), the sesame chicken was tender and flavor packed. Eggs rolls had a five spice type seasoning, delicious.

Latest visit, not so much. Chewy dark meat, egg roll tasted stale, wonton soup was flavorless and mostly wonton without any meat mix inside.

text:
*Editing review after receiving such a nice reply from the restaurant. It appears that my experience was mainly caused by the app and not the restaurant itself. I would still recommend contacting customers directly just to make sure they understand the status of their orders, but I do appreciate the response and the kindness of the business in regard to this review.*

I have ordered from this place 3 times and never had a good experience.  The food is fine, but the delivery leaves a lot to be desired.

The first two times I ordered, delivery took over 90 minutes both times. I went months without ordering and then ordered again tonight, hoping that the other times were a fluke. I use the app Beyond Menu to order from local Chinese places. Anyway, after waiting another 1.5 hours for this order (I would have called sooner but got distracted with playing with my son), I called them to check on the situation.  They told me they had canceled the order. üòØ The man said it was out of their delivery zone (even though they had delivered to me before), and so he immediately canceled it. Thing is, no one ever notified me. He told me Beyond Menu should have notified me.

After I hung up with him, I called Beyond Menu to make sure I wasn't going to be charged for this. I told them the situation and they explained that when he canceled the order through them, he said "customer has been notified". So I waited for 90 minutes for an order that wasn't coming and yet, no one could even give me a phone call to let me know.

Maybe if you're picking up, it's a better experience.  But not worth it to me. We'll stick to Stir Fry Chinese from now on.

address: 4830 Virginia Beach Blvd, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text: For right at $70 I am extremely disappointed! I ordered a Bento box with California roll, tempura vegetables and teriyaki chicken with fried rice. My wife order hibachi steak and chicken with fried rice. We also ordered the pick 2 sushi rolls with spicy California roll as well as happy face roll. All this was to go. ALL sushi was extremely fishy, not just in taste but even smelled fishy. Everyone knows California roll is NOT supposed to be fishy in any way or form. The tempura vegetables were so soaked in oil they were inedible. My teriyaki chicken was very bland. Both of our "fried" rices were far from fried. They look like maybe either brown rice or they added soy sauce to make the rice turn brown possibly. My wife's steak and chicken was ok but not all that. Needless to say we threw it all out and went to Taco Bell lol. Heck we even tried to feed our dogs the chicken and steak and they would not even touch either! The fried ice cream and the salads were the only things that was edible. In today's economy it's sad to spend this much to "treat" ourselves to a meal out and be hugely disappointed like we were.

title: Jade Villa Chinese Restaurant
address: 353 Independence Blvd, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text: First off I want to say the service was excellent. It took me almost no time to get seated, the waitstaff were attentive and the food came quickly. I should specify I went at a time when I don‚Äôt think they were too busy but still the service was very good. As for the food I had some lo-mein, steamed buns and the sticky rice wrapped in a lotus leaf. The lo-mein was good, nothing to scream from the rooftops about but definitely enjoyable. The steamed buns were tasty as heck, as was the sticky rice. The buns balanced the sweetness of the dumpling with the savory flavor of the filling, my one criticism was that it felt like it could have used a bit of spice but i just added some of the chili sauce they had on the table to it and it was all good. The sticky rice was tasty, with the umami flavor from the filling suffusing the rice in a way I enjoyed immensely. Overall when compared to other dim-sum restaurants I‚Äôve been to this restaurant is pretty good. However when taking into account the location of this restaurant this restaurant goes from good to pretty darn great. Overall I wholeheartedly recommend

title: Jade Villa Chinese Restaurant
address: 353 Independence Blvd, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text: It was my second time here, and I felt so compelled to leave this review. Both times, I went for the weekend dimsum, which runs from 12-3pm, but with different individuals. The first time, I went with a coworker at noon and everything was good that I considered bringing a family member here during his spring break. However, my second visit was very different. This time, we went at around 1 pm and got seated immediately since there was quite a number of available tables. The dimsum carts came around, and we picked up a few items. However, most of them were cold and not even lukewarm. Then not too long afterwards, a fairly young woman with the soup cart stopped by our table. We decided to try one of the soups. However, right before serving us the soup, she sneezed and coughed into her hands. She sneezed multiple times throughout and did not even wear a mask. This sight was difficult for us to process at the time. Right after she set the bowl onto our table, I told another server that we don‚Äôt want the soup anymore and told him what the soup server did. Not too long afterwards, another older woman, presumably the manager, came over. She tried to guilt trip us into consuming the soup by saying, ‚Äúshe is going to have to pay if you don‚Äôt want it.‚Äù My family member told her that she sneezed directly into her hands. The older woman took the soup away and crossed it off from our check. I would like to ask, would they eat something someone else had sneezed on? The lady explained that the soup server had come from China just one month ago, so ‚Äúshe did not know and is new [to America].‚Äù She was probably getting paid under the table with cash. Maybe about five minutes later, the soup server came out again and started going around serving soups and coughing and sneezing. This whole thing with the soup server killed our appetites. My second time shows that this restaurant does not have any regard for its diners especially when people‚Äôs memory of Covid is still fresh. Besides, the food was not good at all with most of them being cold and with limited options. Very disappointing and will not be back. If you eat here, dine at your own risk. Who knows what actually goes on behind the scenes in the kitchen? If this place was good in the past, it has spiraled downward very quickly. Maybe that is why it was easy to be seated during what should have been a busy lunch time.

title: Suphan Thai Cuisine
address: 928 Diamond Springs Rd Suite 112, Virginia Beach, VA 23455
text:
A Hidden Gem ‚Äì Suphan Thai Delivers Excellence!

Suphan Thai is nothing short of exceptional. From the moment you walk in, you‚Äôre greeted with warm smiles and a welcoming atmosphere that sets the tone for a truly authentic Thai dining experience in a casual spot.

The food is phenomenal ‚Äî bursting with rich, layered flavors that transport you straight to Thailand. Every dish feels lovingly crafted, from the perfectly balanced Pad Thai to the soul-warming curries and vibrant, fresh appetizers. You can tell the ingredients are top quality, and the attention to detail is second to none.

What truly sets Suphan Thai apart, though, is the people. The staff are incredibly kind, attentive, and genuinely care about making your experience special. It‚Äôs the kind of service that makes you feel like family ‚Äî friendly without being overbearing, and always eager to share a recommendation or a smile.

If you‚Äôre looking for authentic Thai cuisine served by some of the nicest people you‚Äôll ever meet, Suphan Thai is the place.

address: 928 Diamond Springs Rd Suite 112, Virginia Beach, VA 23455
text: We were passing by VA and saw this place was well rated among Thai restaurants. Ordered tom yum fried rice and pad see ew, both of which were spectacular. They offer 5 spice levels for most of their food. My partner got the pad see ew at a 4/5 spice, which seemed to be overwhelmingly spicy. My tom yum fried rice was 3/5 spice, which I thought was spot on as an Asian. They do not play about their spice levels! Phone line seems to have some issues, my first call was disconnected and all the other calls I placed afterwards did not go through. I would definitely come here again!

text: I wanted to start off by how amazing the front of the house staff is but other than that I would not eat here again. I ordered a bento box with shrimp tempura roll, fried rice, and gyoza. It also came with miso soup and salad. The fried rice was barely fried and cold. I also found it very weird that there was corn in it. My gyoza was still partly frozen. The dressing with the salad was watered down to the point you could not taste the dressing. My shrimp tempura roll was just shrimp and rice, nothing else inside and I asked for crunchy onion topping on my shrimp roll as I was advised they had it but instead got a crunchy crumble topping. They also didn't have any descriptions of the rolls other then some of the special ones and it seems like no one but the manager (who was not available) is knowledgeable about what is in the rolls which is not helpful when ordering.  I wouldn't be so upset if they were busy but I came at lunch time and the place was a ghost town. This is not my first time at Volcano just at this location and it was extremely disappointing.

title: Suphan Thai Cuisine
address: 928 Diamond Springs Rd Suite 112, Virginia Beach, VA 23455
text:
This dining destination truly has it all; outstanding cuisine, exceptional service, and a soothing environment. The owners' kindness and commitment to preparing every dish to order ensure a memorable experience, well worth the wait. The flavors throughout the menu are uniformly impressive;
For appetizers we got the papaya salad's, it inclusion of tomatoes and shrimp proves a thoughtful and effective enhancement.
Then we also got the lettuce wrap and it was exceptionally delicious. It possessed a distinct flavor profile, prompting us to inquire about its ingredients with the owner. Notably, the combination of lemon grass and kaffir lime leaves contributed to its unique and addictive taste.
For the main course, we shared the stir-fry chicken basil, which was exceptionally flavorful and freshly prepared!
For dessert, our favorite sticky rice with mango was just right - perfect sweetness and so fresh!
Also, if you like a little kick, it's recommended to get level 1 - just right and addicting!
Everything here is delicious and prepared fresh.
The most authentic Thai food I've ever had!!!

title: Suphan Thai Cuisine
address: 928 Diamond Springs Rd Suite 112, Virginia Beach, VA 23455

address: 928 Diamond Springs Rd Suite 112, Virginia Beach, VA 23455
text: Over the years we have enjoyed Thai Food at many different restaurants in several states. We usually go at least once a week or so. Suphan Thai is simply one of the best we have ever experienced and after dining here several times we are absolutely fans of this restaurant. The owner/chef Cathy strives to use the freshest ingredients possible, and her dishes are perfectly spiced. We just enjoyed another amazing meal this evening - Drunken Noodles, and Oxtail soup. The broth in the soup was simply the best we have ever tasted. If you're looking for truly outstanding Thai food, this is the place.

text: This is the second time I have parked, walked in, and asked for a 5 pk of fresh chicken nuggets and a small chicken noodle soup. Right after I received my change, my food was handed in a bag. They did not ask if I was going to dine-in... I asked them if my nuggets were straight from the grease and was assured they were. NOPE, THEY WERE WARM, BUT NOT HOT! As much as one pays for fast food or just food in general, we should receive what we ask for even if we have to wait. I have no problem with that! It's the fact that they looked me in the face and said they just came up. Came up from the hot box, but not the grease! If you want my business, you must earn it, and please do not lie to my face when you know that they didn't! The Mgr was quick to take my bag and place it in the trash and said it would be a few minutes. I waited and received what I paid for, but as far as an apology or saying something to me about their mess up, silence was what I received! When I finally got handed the bag, I didn't receive the sauce that I asked for for the nuggets. The Mgr. was irritated and placed two in the bag as if I was wrong for asking! No, thank you, come again, he just went to a young lady that was on her phone, and they continued their conversation. GET IT TOGETHER, CHICK-FIL-A! You may be the only place that serves REAL chicken, but that does not mean that an Ole lady like myself will not go back! AND IT IS WORD OF MOUTH THAT WILL GIVE OR TAKE BUSINESS FROM YOU! The younger generation is so intrigued with what is on their phones that they have forgotten what they are supposed to do, and that is CUSTOMER SERVICE AND THEIR JOB! title: Suphan Thai Cuisine
address: 928 Diamond Springs Rd Suite 112, Virginia Beach, VA 23455
text:
Ah, Suphan Tai Cuisine. An elusive dance of sweet, spicy, sour, and savory‚Äîonly a true orchestrator can bring such elements into harmonious balance. And yet, my dear readers, I must admit that my recent encounter with this particular establishment was not defined by the cuisine itself, but rather by the circumstances that prevented me from indulging in it. You see, I did not eat there. No tantalizing aroma wafted from my plate, no morsel graced my taste buds. However, it is not the absence of food that defines this review but rather the presence of something equally nourishing‚Äîthe spirit of welcome.

From the moment I stepped foot onto Suphan Tai Cuisine's charming exterior, I was enveloped by an atmosphere that was warm, unpretentious, and, dare I say, inviting. The staff, though deprived of the chance to present their culinary prowess, demonstrated hospitality of the rarest kind‚Äîhospitality that extends beyond the meal itself. They offered me not a menu, but a smile; not a dish, but an experience. They permitted me to capture the essence of their establishment in a photograph‚Äîa gesture that, though small, spoke volumes.

I may not have dined within their walls on this occasion, but it was made clear to me that Suphan Tai Cuisine is a place worth returning to‚Äîa place where kindness is served alongside the food, and the ambiance lingers long after you‚Äôve left. Indeed, my journey here is not complete, and it is with great anticipation that I shall return, eager to partake in the symphony of flavors that await. Until then, I carry with me the memory of a welcome so genuine that it almost felt like a meal in itself.

title: Denny's
address: 6360 Newtown Rd, Norfolk, VA 23502
text:
As a restaurant owner, I hate leaving bad reviews, but sometimes they are warranted.  I arrived about 1030am on a Sunday and the restaurant was dead. I was seated at a booth that had crumbs all over the seats, I looked around and all the other tables were this way.  Crumbs also littered the entire floor.  The waitress brought my coffee which had clearly been sitting on the warmer for far too long.  When I finally got my order in it took forever to come out, and unfortunately came out cold.  I sucked it up for the most part but the biscuits and gravy were bitter and ice cold.  No sight of my waitress, never bothered to ask how things are, finally someone asked to remove my empty plates and I asked about getting the biscuits heated up.  This of course took forever too and still no sign of my waitress.  Finally I got up to go to the register to pay.  This is about the only saving grace, someone finally came to help me and when I asked to just pay for my food they said not to worry about it.

Save your money and time and go elsewhere.  It is obvious this store needs an entire overhaul and new management who will hold their staff accountable.

title: Suphan Thai Cuisine
address: 928 Diamond Springs Rd Suite 112, Virginia Beach, VA 23455
text: My first time at Suphan Thai. Lunch today with my brother. Not crowded, seated immediately. Very friendly, helpful, and cheerful staff. Ordered Som Tom (green papaya salad), Singapore rice noodles with vegetables, and green curry with vegetables. The Som Tom was delicious, very traditional Thai. I love that the chef used ripe cherry tomatoes, very nice! The Singapore rice noodles were delicious, very full of vegetables and flavorful. I ordered spice level 3 out of 5 for my entrees. The green curry was excellent! Not overly sweet and again, very traditional Thai style with baby eggplants and lots of vegetables, exactly how I like it. The owner/server was so friendly and nice. The flavors here reminded me of when I lived in Thailand. I will return again soon.

title: Thee Soulfood Kitchen
address: 5957 E Virginia Beach Blvd, Norfolk, VA 23502
text:
I've ordered from here quite a few times. The fried chicken is always good. That's normally my go to, and they have a great lunch special where you can get three wings and two sides.

The food here is hit or miss in my opinion. Three items in particular that tend to be good some days and bad other days include the macaroni and cheese, the yams, and the turkey wings.

Sometimes the yams are delicious and other days they're mushy and dry. The last time my mother ordered them, she said the yams tasted like they were days old. The turkey wings are also dry sometimes. I personally think some of their dishes being dry may have something to do with the heat lamp the food is sitting under. I think it dries certain foods out.

The mac and cheese has its inconsistencies too. Today, we picked up a half tray of mac and cheese and green beans. The green beans were OK, but the mac and cheese was watery and tasted like they added too much pepper. My sister had to add more cheese, garlic and onion powder, and smoked paprika, then baked it a little longer. Our family said it tasted much better after she made some changes.

I would go back for individual meals but not for catering. The quality of the food is just too inconsistent to rely on for events, sadly.

title: Domino's Pizza
address: 368 Newtown Rd, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text:
I have ordered from here twice. Both times, I never got my order. The first time, they closed at midnight and I ordered at 9:30 or so, it got to quality check, was there for an hour+ then it was cancelled at 11. It wasn't even midnight yet. And I ordered HOURS before closing time. The second time, was tonight, I ordered nearly 2 hours ago, the food was made fast, but it sat in quality check for 1.5 hrs of that 2 hours and they only had 1 driver, which honestly. Regardless how many deliveries you have. It shouldn't take almost 2 hrs for a driver to complete a few deliveries. So I call to ask if it could be remade and get to me soon, or would I have to wait ANOTHER nearly 2 hours to which they said, yes they could remake it. But it would probably be the same amount of time. And honestly. I won't be ordering from here again. 0-2, all the staff needs to be fired and new staff hired because none of them clearly know how to run an efficient store nor do they know wth is going on apparently.

-someone who's worked fast food for almost a decade.

title: Shake Shack Virginia Beach
address: 296 Constitution Dr, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text:
Unique and delicious burgers, fries, and shakes; lots of fun options at a decent value. Black truffle parmesan fries very nice, love the truffle sauce. 'Shroom burger is outstanding, quite big, perfectly fried, and plenty of cheese. Can't go wrong with the Black Truffle and SmokeShack burgers as well, hearty and flavorful. Holiday-themed shakes (Christmas Cookie, Apple Cider Donut, and Chocolate Yule Log) were all fantastic, very rich!

Update 06/2025 - Fried pickles, Oreo Funnel Cake Shake, and Campfire S'mores Shake are all also great!

title: Suphan Thai Cuisine
address: 928 Diamond Springs Rd Suite 112, Virginia Beach, VA 23455
text:
Really amazing all around. The best, most authentic, most flavorful Thai food my husband and I have found in the area. Hands down the closest to the food we ate in Bangkok. Cathy the owner is cooking right in sight, and her daughter Ashley is so incredibly helpful and kind. We went with our two year old son, and they had a child's fork for him and were wonderful sports about him loudly squealing about how much he loved his food.

We had the larb (great flavor), pad Thai (actually contains vegetables!! Amazing amount of flavor compared to the rather bland version often offered), red curry (lots of vegetables, well seasoned, incredibly flavorful) and sticky rice (absolutely perfect - I think we finished it in 30 seconds).

Highly recommend.

title: Ashley's On Greenwich
address: 5655 Greenwich Rd, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text: Ashley's is a comfortable and nicely appointed bar/restaurant inside the Holiday Inn on Greenwich Rd. The service was excellent, the seating comfortable, and the food was tasty.  The menu is a bit limited, and a bit pricey compared to similar restaurants, i.e. Ruby Tuesday's, Applebee's, Chili's,  etc. We both had the classic burger with fries. Mine medium rare, and my friend's medium, and they were cooked perfectly! The fries were good and semi crispy, not soggy at all, and they had some kind of seasoning on them reminiscent of bbq potato chips. The burgers came with lettuce, tomato and red onion,  with mayo on the side, and a dill pickle spear. I lucked out because my friend doesn't like onions or dill pickles, so I got hers! Our burger meals were $11 each. Any other menu options were similarly priced or higher. They don't have good prices on wine or beer or cocktails,  so we just opted for ice water, which was regularly refilled. Our server was prompt, professional and informative, and our food came out within 8-10 minutes. We were the only table for lunch, but they were doing a brisk take out business at the hostess stand, and there were a couple of people at the bar. Nice place for basic bar food in a comfortable and quiet setting. Service stood out more than the food. We may go again because it is so close to my office, but we will probably get salads with chicken or salmon, or perhaps 2 appetizers to share, like quesadillas and sliders.  Great option if you're staying at that hotel, as they offer breakfast, lunch and dinner. AND the ladies restroom was very nice, and clean! Lol.

title: Topgolf Virginia Beach
address: 5444 Greenwich Rd, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text:
Tonight my family and I were at top golf to celebrate my brothers birthday. From start to finish I had a wonderful time. Although I did notice that the bar was understaffed, especially for a holiday weekend. But I also recognize and understand that staff may have called out for the holiday weekend. Beyond that, it was a great evening!!!

Every. Single. Staff member that I came in contact with tonight met me with a positive attitude and a smile. Anything that slightly went misarray was dealt with and handled with care, compassion, and a smile.
Tonight the entire grid that va beach top golf was on lost power. The staff was prompt to check on and care for and update the guests on what to expect, continuously and frequently, while also maintaining a smile and positivity. From front desk check in staff, to bartenders, to food runners, to servers, to busters, to management, and anyone there that was working went above and beyond to ensure that all guests were taken care of, communicated with, and made to feel safe.

As someone who has been in the industry for many years, I am so HAPPY, PROUD, ELATED, FIST PUMPS IN THE AIR!!!! (It‚Äôs tee shirt time) of how this establishment handled the fiasco of losing power. They worked as a team and kept smiles on their faces.

Top golf also did not charge us for our ‚Äúbay rental‚Äù and are covering all tabs (at least for my ‚Äúparty‚Äù as far as I know) and I was astonished by this act. This is something the company should be proud of, even if it means losing out sometimes. Instead of being ‚Äúmoney hungry‚Äù they made sure everyone there was FIRST AND FOREMOST ***SAFE**** but they also did not allow the stress and pressure of a MAJOR power outage ruin their guests nights. And that says A LOT for a major corporation.

****** But the immediate MANAGEMENT AND STAFF IS WHO DESERVE ALL THIS CREDIT!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!  ******** THEY ARE THE ONES WHO HAVE MADE THIS LOCATION STAND OUT!!!! And if it were not for our local neighbors and community working here, it wouldn‚Äôt be what it is! ******

SO DONT FORGET THAT CORPORATE!!! IT IS **OUR LOCALS** DOING THIS AND PROVIDING A WONDERFUL EXPERIENCE!!!!!!
They are absolute ROCKSTARS!!!!!

I HOPE YOU ARE ALL PROUD OF YOURSELVES TONIGHT!!!!! <3
(Because you absolutely should be!)

My family was in booth 229 & 230 this evening (8/30/2025) and I would also like to highlight how wonderful and kind our server was tonight. I don‚Äôt remember his name but I do want to make sure he is recognized in this post. Our family thought you did an amazing job tonight and you killed it dude!!! Keep up that same professionalism throughout life and you WILL GO FAR!!!! he was an absolute RoCKsTaR!!!!

Thank you VIRGINIA BEACH TOP GOLF for showing kindness and compassion this evening.  For being prompt to respond to an emergency and to also keep us all *very frequently*  updated with the evening as you all navigated this unexpected disturbance in the night.

You all freaking killed it tonight!!! You all make an amazing team!!! And I‚Äôm proud of you all!!!

Thank you! Thank you! Thank you!!

And keep up the great work!!

Talk to server and ‚Äúoh yeah we can take care of it. Order our drinks, and drinks get dropped off. Wait another 20 minutes for him to come back so we can say we‚Äôd like to order food. text:

Pizza was not as expected.

There was no buttery flavored sauce that's supposed to be on the outside crust (on both pizzas). I ordered EXTRA pepperoni, but the pizzas had light pepperoni. ALL THE TOPPINGS WERE LIGHT, or almost none. Both pizzas were Meatzza (all the meats) pizzas, but the 2nd pizza had almost no meat. The dough was good and soft; not burnt.

Hopefully, the reason the cook made the mistakes is maybe they were very tired or having a rough day, instead of the cook's reason for the bad pizza being that they were careless. I like to give people a fair chance. I'm not perfect, either.

title: Thee Soulfood Kitchen
address: 5957 E Virginia Beach Blvd, Norfolk, VA 23502
text:
Before talking about the food, I can't get past the long wait. We waited in line at least 20-30 min in line just to order, followed by about 10 minutes to get our food (2 dinners and one extra side) for takeout. I'm used to waiting at these kinds of places but what I couldn't understand was why the wait was so long if the food was ready made. There was also a significant amount of time when they weren't taking people from the takeout line, so I guess they were either understaffed or primarily getting food for dine-in customers before moving to the take-out line. It was extremely annoying at the time....

That being said, I'm so glad the food was at least worth it. I decided to try the turkey wings because they looked huge and had a great brown color across the glass. They definitely looked as good as they tasted! The meat was so tender and flavorful and slid right off the bones! The gravy was delicious too! The sides were also pretty good - the rice and gravy was tasty and the mac and cheese wasn't too cheesey, which I prefer. I was sad that they didn't have green beans as indicated on the menu, so I'm glad the mac and cheese was at least good.

Overall, I'm glad the food was good! I just would not come here if I'm really hunger because the wait is brutal.

title: Topgolf Virginia Beach
address: 5444 Greenwich Rd, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text:
This a really solid top golf location. The staff, food, golfing, and environment were all excellent. As a non-golfer, can‚Äôt speak too much about the atmosphere or golfing, but to me it felt amazing! What I can comment on is the customer service and the food!!!

I don‚Äôt usually write reviews, but just as a token of proof to build on what I said: My family was there on vacation and we love top golf! We had ordered food, but for whatever reason it got slightly delayed and our time was about to run out due to the wait. As a result, management came over, gave us a personal apology, 30 additional free minutes to our time, and you could tell they felt bad and were truly sorry about what had happened. The food was also amazing too!

Depending on the person, delay in food can seem like a bad thing (were human, these things happen) or it can seem like a silly thing (not the end of the world). Either way, it‚Äôs so rare for me to experience staff at this high of a level who truly showed empathy, kindness, and guilt from the experience, so I had to write a review about it. Thanks for reading, you guys definitely need to go here! It was a blast.

title: Topgolf Virginia Beach
address: 5444 Greenwich Rd, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text:
We usually have a great experience at Topgolf and were really looking forward to celebrating Father‚Äôs Day there. While the initial reservation process was smooth, the experience trying to modify it was incredibly frustrating‚Äîand the lack of local customer service support made it worse.

Days in advance, I booked two bays online. After some friends canceled, we only needed one. Wanting to free up the second bay for someone else, I called to make the change. The representative informed me that she couldn‚Äôt modify the reservation‚ÄîI‚Äôd need to cancel and rebook entirely. She assured me there was still availability at 4:00 PM and that my $60 deposit would be refunded immediately.

Trusting that, I canceled the reservation. When I attempted to rebook, there were no time slots even close to 4:00 PM. I refreshed the site repeatedly that evening with no luck. By the next morning, the waitlist was full. I called again and spoke with Joseph, who offered no real solution or support.

I completely understand that Father‚Äôs Day is a busy time‚Äîbut I followed the directions I was given and still lost my reservation, with no immediate refund and no help to resolve the issue. I wasn‚Äôt asking for anything free‚Äîjust to use the reservation I had already paid for. Extremely disappointing, especially for a day we were looking forward to.

text: It was around 2 pm on a Monday so it was quiet and quaint. We were seated immediately and our waitress came to our table quickly as well. Our waitress ( I hope I'm spelling her name correctly) Katera was exceptionally, outstanding! She was pleasant, personable, and professional. Our food was freshly made, hot, and fried to perfection! I got the catfish basket with sweet potato waffle fries and my mom got the shrimp basket with 3 boiled potatoes and the cajun rice sans sausage. I gave my mom one piece of catfish (which were nice and large) in exchange for two shrimp, also large. The catfish crust was flaky while the meat was wonderfully tender. The shrimp too was fried and seasoned to perfection. The Cajun rice was delish with shrimp and egg and something deliciously chewy that we just assumed was chicken or some other kind of seafood. The music playing was all 90s to early 2000s R&B classics, which set the entire mood to relax, enjoy, and chill mode. I enjoyed eating here and would highly recommend to any and everyone and can't wait to go back! And to the establishment, please give Katera a raise üòâ

text: We just left this venue and just had to add a review about our awful experience.  We were part of a large party.  My wife and I were there with our granddaughter.  We ordered a flatbread pizza and a kids meal for our granddaughter.  We then watched order after order come out many of which we know were placed after we placed our order.  The waitress never even brought us drinks even after we had asked several times for a glass of water.  After checking again with the waitress who was clearly annoyed with us, we could see that she had forgotten to place our order.  She never once was apologetic and never brought us drinks.  The food was finally delivered by a separate food server and at that point I flagged down the waitress and asked her to get us our check so we could get out of there as quickly as possible.  I tried to explain to her that her service had been very poor and she was quite disrespectful and very annoyed.  I asked her where her manager was and she told me to try to find him.  She was totally disrespectful.  I found the manager and explained how unhappy we were with our experience.  We paid our bill (there was no offer for a discount of any sort but we did not ask for one).  We did not leave a tip at all which is so unusual for us as we are always very generous with our tipping.  Our only hope is that the manager actually spoke with the server so that others would not be subjected to the same type of disrespectful service.

title: Topgolf Virginia Beach
address: 5444 Greenwich Rd, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text:
Came with a big group (5 bays, 6-7 people per bay). My bay had 7 people, and we all ordered at the same time. Everyone got their food and drinks within 20-25 minutes‚Äîexcept me. I ordered just a beer and it took an hour to arrive.

At 30 minutes, I checked in. Our server‚Äîwho was handling all five bays alone‚Äîsaid it was coming. At 45 minutes, I checked again, and a curly-haired kid behind him gave me an attitude: ‚ÄúYou just need to be patient; he‚Äôs the only server for your bays.‚Äù Finally, after a full hour, they told me they didn‚Äôt even have the beer I want and gave me something else instead. Meanwhile, everyone else had already finished their food and drinks.

Two pieces of advice for management:

1. If you're hosting a large group, assign more than one server. It helps both customers and your business.

2. Don‚Äôt hire rude, incompetent staff. One kid was disrespectful‚Äîthen 10 minutes after our interaction, I saw him playing at a bay while his coworker struggled to serve five. Unacceptable.

Our group had fun, but the service was terrible. I wouldn‚Äôt recommend this place, and if it were up to me, I‚Äôd avoid it altogether.

text: I have visited This Old House a several times over the years for both lunch and dinner. Just take a look at the pictures that other diners have shared.  The rice is very mushy so it's very hard to eat it. title: This Old House Japanese Restaurant
address: 309 Aragona Blvd #118, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text:
I was completely misled by the high Google reviews for this sushi restaurant. It felt like a bait-and-switch experience, given its high star rating. Months later, I still vividly recall the disappointment and horror of our meal.

Having enjoyed sushi in California, Asia, and locally in Virginia Beach and Suffolk, I can confidently say this was the worst sushi I‚Äôve ever had. The rolls were poorly constructed, with unevenly cut fish and toppings precariously perched on the rice log. It was a mess from the start.

When we bit into the rolls, the rice was so over-compressed it had the texture of rubber. The raw fish tasted fishy and far from fresh‚Äîa major red flag for sushi. To make matters worse, we made the mistake of ordering uni, which was overwhelmingly fishy and unpleasant. I genuinely struggled to swallow it but felt obligated since we had paid for it.

The only redeeming aspect of the visit was the staff, who were incredibly kind. Unfortunately, the food was so bad that we didn‚Äôt have the heart to tell them. We simply wanted to leave as quickly as possible.

I struggled with whether to write this negative review because I understand how hard it is for small business owners to survive. However, I don‚Äôt want others who have had good sushi to go through the same disappointing experience I did, being misled by the high reviews.

Adding insult to injury, we spent over $100 on this terrible meal, making it even more unforgettable.

Those who rated this place four or five stars must have never had real, good sushi. This was, without question, the most unforgettable sushi experience of my life‚Äîfor all the wrong reasons. I wouldn‚Äôt recommend this place to anyone.

title: Phoenix Restaurant and Lounge
address: 928 Diamond Springs Rd #115, Virginia Beach, VA 23455
text:
I ordered food to go. It was a bit before normal lunchtime. I must say they must be clean because the bleach smell was STRONG. Someone was mopping. I hope she wears a mask in the future. That bleach can have long-term effects, though I do appreciate the cleanliness.
On to the food. I ordered Jerk chicken, cabbage, and plantains. The Jerk chicken was spicy with a hint of sweetness. I was going to eat only half, but ended up eating more.  The cabbage was a bit different. I've had it with carrots before, but it also had bits of green beans. It was different, yet tasty. They were firm, not mushy, which is how I prefer it. The plantains were good. I prefer them with the crispy ends, but they were still soft and sweet.
Overall, I enjoyed the food. I'll have to pop in again.

title: This Old House Japanese Restaurant
address: 309 Aragona Blvd #118, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text:
Very impressive family sushi restaurant with passion for their food! They put the chain sushi restaurants in the area to shame. Here I started with individual pieces of sushi, and then a Virginia Eel Roll with a bowl of miso soup.

The temperature of the fish was slightly chilled below room temp, so as you eat, it gets to the right temperature for eating sushi. The quality was quite good, not Tsukiji Market good, but good for this region of the US. The rice was at the perfect temp, however, the texture could use improvement. And of course, extremely generous amounts of fish.

It seems like they actually make their miso soup with paste rather than the cheap powdered soup, which is very rare. Only it needs to be tuned down a bit(too much miso), then it'd be perfect.

The hole in the wall vibe is very reminiscent to restaurants in Japan, with menu items posted on the wall. If you lived in Japan before, then this place will give you a bit of notalgia, as if you're walking through the alleys of Yokosuka.

So if you are in the mood for sushi, don't spend your fortune at a restaurant that feeds you more rice than fish, and fish more frozen than chilled.

Trust your local Asian food snob and Come visit This Old House!

title: Charleys Cheesesteaks and Wings
address: 556 Newtown Rd, Virginia Beach, VA 23462
text:
For it being my FIRST time coming to this establishment, and I went through Drive-thru, the cashier did not great me, read back my order, and had the nerve to point out that I could leave her a tip while using my apple pay. Now, I am old school, and I tip heavily when a service has been rendered or performed, but she is a cashier... she is getting paid an hourly amount to make a drink and place napkins and condiments in the bag to which the food was placed by the other male standing in front of the grill. What service did she perform on me to receive a 10% all the way up to 30% tip for a cheesesteak, fries, and a Sprite? ü§î She didn't acknowledge me as a patron, nor welcomed me to Charlie's. She did not ask me if I needed any extra napkins or any  extra condiments, I had to ask for them. What makes it bad was the cheesesteak was on point, but the fries were not hot and when I asked for Cajun seasoning on them, it looked like they took the shaker and gave them a heavy dose of seasoning just on the top of the fries. There was no seasoning around them or on the fries on the bottom of the box.
Now, you tell me... did she deserve a tip? If I am wrong, I'll admit it, but in this case, it's not like I got a manicure while waiting for my food or she personally came out to give me my food. I was told to wait for 4 minutes for new ones to be made, and I politely told her I did not have the time. Mind you, it is 5:37 p.m. and there is NO reason any establishment should be serving luke warm (at best) fries with seasoning not on each individual fry at this time, which is called dinner or super time! The prices were extremely overpriced, especially for the quantity of fries that you receive. I do not believe in giving my hard earned money to a woman who paid no attention to me, did not greet me, nor asked me if I needed any extra napkins or condiments. I will not tip because you are at your job and doing a horrible representation of what a cashier is supposed to do regardless of where you work. BTW, I paid $21.78 for a regular cheesesteak, fries, and a medium drink!
To the manager of this establishment, if you plan on keeping this place open, you may want to retrain your cashier staff and your cook online. No one should be given fries that are not fresh paying the prices that Charlie's charges! Much luck to you and this business.
